title: Man found guilty in 30-year-old cold case involving Toronto single mother
description:
Thirty years after single mother Barbara Brodkin was found stabbed to death in her midtown Toronto apartment, the man arrested by Toronto police cold case investigators has been convicted of second-degree murder.

Charles Mustard, 69, expressed disbelief after Superior Court Justice Brian OтАЩMarra told him he had been found guilty and was revoking his bail.

тАЬI didnтАЩt kill Barbara,тАЭ Mustard said repeatedly as he was handcuffed and led out of the downtown Toronto courtroom.
 
A sentencing hearing for Mustard is scheduled for next month. Catherine McDonald has more.

title: Agression rwandaise : Reprise des affrontements sur lтАЩaxe Rwindi/kanyabayonga ce dimanche 26/5/24
description:
Agression rwandaise : Reprise des affrontements sur lтАЩaxe Rwindi/kanyabayonga ce dimanche 26/5/24

Reprise des affrontements dans le Rutshuru ce dimanche entre les FARDC et les M23. Des sources locales affirment que de fortes d├йtonations d'armes sont entendues depuis 5 heures sur l'axe Rwindi--Kanyabayonga en plein Parc national des Virunga dans le territoire de Rutshuru. Les m├кmes sources ajoutent que ces tirs sont entendus dans la zone de Kitolu, une colline situ├йe ├а moins de 3 kilom├иtres au Nord de l'agglom├йration de Kibirizi. Pendant ce temps, un calme pr├йcaire r├иgne dans le Masisi o├╣ les FARDC ont r├йcup├йr├й plusieurs villages, selon des sources locales.

en fin, Sultani Makenga de la coalition M23_RDF_AFC ├йvoque les points saillants de ce que demande la rebellion ├а Kinshasa. " Nous sommes partis officiellement ├а Kinshasa et nous sommes revenus officiellement. Nous avons visit├й Mbanzangu et nous avons particip├й dans plusieurs r├йunions. Nous nous sommes convenus que nous allons former une forcer bas├йe au Nord et au Sud Kivu pour la paix chez nous et que nos fr├иres retournent au pays. Une autre force devrait aller ├а Kinshasa,..."

Alors que les rebelles du M23 continuent de gagner du terrain en province du Nord-Kivu, lтАЩancien s├йnateur C├йlestin Vunabandi privil├йgie la voie militaire contre le Rwanda. Il rejette cat├йgoriquement lтАЩid├йe de n├йgocier avec les rebelles. ┬л Je ne suis pas s├╗r que nous pouvons finir cette guerre par seulement la n├йgociation comme certains le disent avec le Rwanda, non. Le Rwanda a suffisamment montr├й sa mauvaise foi. Il faut, je crois, lui apporter la preuve que nous avons la capacit├й de le chasser hors du territoire national, et alors, ├а ce moment-l├а, nous pourrons dialoguer. Par contre, en ce qui concerne ces suppl├йtifs, notamment le M23, ma position a toujours ├йt├й quтАЩil nтАЩy a pas de n├йgociations possibles avec ces gens-l├а. Ce sont des suppl├йtifs, de simples individus que le Rwanda utilise. Le jour o├╣ nous aurons trouv├й une solution avec le Rwanda, ils dispara├оtront. Nous avons une exp├йrience de tout cela : nous l'avons v├йcu en 2009 avec le CNDP, nous avons vu comment la guerre sтАЩest termin├йe. Nous avons v├йcu la m├кme exp├йrience avec le M23 en 2012, donc cela finira de la m├кme mani├иre si nous trouvons une solution, notamment militaire ou m├кme diplomatique. En tout cas, cela sera avec le pays qui nous agresse, surtout leur apporter la preuve que nous avons les moyens de les chasser hors du territoire national ┬╗, a d├йclar├й le s├йnateur C├йlestin Vunabandi ├а ACTUALITE.CD. Depuis la r├йsurgence de la r├йbellion du M23, la R├йpublique D├йmocratique du Congo accuse le Rwanda d'├кtre ├а l'origine de la d├йt├йrioration de la situation s├йcuritaire et humanitaire dans l'Est du pays ├а travers l'activisme des rebelles du M23. Le 3 mai dernier, la diplomatie am├йricaine avait ├йgalement accus├й le Rwanda d'├кtre ├а l'origine d'un bombardement meurtrier sur un camp de d├йplac├йs ├а Goma.

M├йfiez vous de cette information. Kanyabayonga est enti├иrement sous le contr├┤le de l'arm├йe congolaise, un convoi humanitaire du CICR est arriv├й dans la cit├й hier pour distribuer l'aide aux d├йplac├йs et tout se passe bien. L'auteur de la publication Simaro Ngongo a supprim├й son contenu quand il a constat├й que le mensonge ├йtait insupportable par ses abonn├йs. 

Apr├иs avoir ├йt├й re├зu en grande pompe en RDC, Muhoozi Kainerugaba, chef des arm├йes ougandaises et fils de Museveni, s'est rendu au pays de son oncle Paul Kagame, le Rwanda, pour renforcer les liens entre les arm├йes ougandaise et rwandaise.

title: Ali Abulaban double murder trial | Jury begins deliberation
description:
Closing arguments began Friday in the trial of a man charged with murdering his wife and another man by shooting them inside the couple's East Village apartment.

Ali Abulaban, 32, who was known in online circles as a content creator dubbed "JinnKid," faces life in prison without the possibility of parole if convicted of the Oct. 21, 2021, slayings of Ana Abulaban, 28, and Rayburn Cardenas Barron, 29.

Prosecutors allege Abulaban killed both victims because he was angered that his wife no longer wanted to remain married to him.

Deputy District Attorney Taren Brast told jurors that Ana Abulaban made it clear she was through with Ali Abulaban following multiple incidents of domestic violence and Ali Abulaban's sexual encounter with another woman.

title: Wrongfully convicted man walks free in murder cold case
description: Jack McCullough walked out of an Illinois courtroom a free man Friday, after being exonerated in a decades-old murder case he didn't commit. The strange case included McCullough being accused of the crime by his own mother in a deathbed confession, even though he had an alibi. Erin Moriarty reports.

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. title: COLDCASE De moord op Geert de Raeymaeker
description:
De moord op Geert de Raeymaeker staat deze week centraal in Bureau Rijnmond. Hij wordt in de nacht van 29 op 30 maart 2003 vermoord in Rotterdam. De zaak is nooit opgelost en is nu ├й├йn de zaken van de Cold Casekalender, die OM en politie alsnog tot een goed einde willen brengen. Temeer omdat het de levens van de ouders van Geert, inmiddels 86 en 90 jaar oud, nog dagelijks beheerst.

De 36-jarige Geert heeft de florerende uitbenerij van zijn vader in het Belgische Boom overgenomen en houdt van het leven. Hij is geregeld in Rotterdam, waar zijn vriend Osman woont. 
De avond voor de moord eten Geert en Osman samen met hun partners wat in Rotterdam. De vrouwen vertrekken en Osman en Geert gaan naar een woning in de Hennewierstraat. 

Ze bestellen een escortdame. Als er wordt gebeld staat er geen vrouw voor de deur maar twee mannen, die Geert met zestien kogels om het leven brengen. Osman, die in het drugscircuit zit,  vlucht naar boven en wordt alleen geraakt in zijn been. De politie vermoedt direct dat Osman meer weet over de moord op Geert maar dat spoor loopt, net als andere scenarioтАЩs, dood. In 2017 overlijdt Osman. 

Een kerkhof in Boom is de laatste rustplaats van Geert. Hij ligt daar vlakbij zijn broer, die op 56-jarige leeftijd overleed aan een hartstilstand. Politie en OM hopen dat er mensen zijn die de zaak los kunnen trekken en informatie hebben, hoe ogenschijnlijk klein dan ook. Er is een beloning van 15 duizend euro uitgeloofd.

title: Dinosaur Cold Case
description: It's called Borealopelta, a recently discovered, 110-million-year-old dinosaur that's so well preserved, it looks like it could've been walking the Earth just last month. Now, paleontologists at Canada's Royal Tyrrell Museum have taken on the roles of forensic detectives to determine where it came from, how it died, and why this land-based creature wound up in an area that was once an inland sea. Join the investigation as we paint a picture of the dinosaur's world and the environmental and predatory foes that may have ended its life.

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Murder Suspect Makes Daring Escape from Oregon Courthouse Before Trial
description:
Newly released security camera footage shows a 28-year-old murder suspect in Oregon escaping from the courthouse moments after his hands and legs were unshackled. Eli Villalobos was preparing to stand trial on multiple felony charges, including second-degree murder in the 2021 fatal stabbing of 33-year-old Artemio Guzman-Olvera. After a two-hour manhunt, Villalobos was found hiding under a blanket in a closet of an apartment after a caller reported seeing a man trying to break in a neighboring unit. Villalobos was taken into custody and later indicted on two additional counts of first-degree burglary and one count of second-degree escape.

David Swift is accused of murdering his wife, Karen Swift, in October 2011, after she was found dead in an old Tennessee cemetery. David was allegedly the last person to see her alive after she returned home from a Halloween party. When David was arrested, he had remarried and was living with another woman in Alabama. David has been charged with premeditated first-degree murder and could face life behind bars.

title: 23-Year-Old FBI Cold Case Solved Truck Removed From River (Most Dangerous Recovery to date)
description:
On this episode of Chaos Divers, we were joined by Depths of History as we headed back to the Ohio Valley to clear the Steubenville Marina of the 13 vehicles located and remove an incredible piece of evidence for the FBI and the Jefferson County SheriffтАЩs office.

23-Year-Old FBI Cold Case Solved Truck Removed From River (Most Dangerous Recovery to date)
During our previous searches for Karen Adams, we located the truck that we believed belonged to Charles Hanlon, missing for 23 years. As we cleared the vehicles, our focus was on removing the truck that could potentially play a large role in helping the FBI close a cold case file that had plagued so many for so long.

This episode is in honor of Sheriff Fred Abdalla, Senior, whom it was a privilege to know and we will be eternally grateful for the opportunity to have worked with him.

title: Crime Patrol - рдХреНрд░рд╛рдЗрдо рдкреЗрдЯреНрд░реЛрд▓ рд╕рддрд░реНрдХ - Episode 485 - 21st March 2015
description:
"Click to watch all the episodes of Crime Patrol - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupza0aEZ_FKj0mBguCdtwU_c

Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, тАЬIt should not have happenedтАЭ.Would knowing the тАЬWhyтАЭ behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he looks at meтАЭ, тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he/she is behavingтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she is out of his/her mindтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she has gone crazyтАЭ. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Murder on the Orient Express (2017) Movie Explained in Hindi Story Summarized
description:
Murder on the Orient Express (2017) Survival movie explained in Hindi Urdu. The Suspense Thriller Survival film тАЬMurder on the Orient Express: Everyone is a SuspectтАЭ story summarized with a full ending explanation. The plot revolves around a clever detective named Hercule Poirot. He was so smart that people from all around the world knew who he was. Hercule had just cracked a tough case in Jerusalem about a very important treasure that was nicked from a church. He worked out that the thief was actually the copper who had asked him to solve the case! Everyone was gobsmacked at how fast Hercule figured it out. But there was no break for Hercule. Straight after that, he hopped on a posh train called the Orient Express to head to London. This train was pretty special, with only a few passengers, making the trip snug and private. On the train, Hercule bumped into a bloke named Richard. Richard was on edge because he found a spooky note saying he was in danger. Richard was no good; he was actually a gangster! Even though Richard offered Hercule a stack of cash to look after him, Hercule said no because he didnтАЩt fancy helping a baddie. One wild and stormy night, the train got stuck due to awful weather. The next morning, everyone realized that Richard was missing, and when they checked his room, they found him dead! Oh dear! There was a huge mystery right on the train. 

Now, the trainтАЩs manager, who was mates with Hercule, asked him to sort out the mystery fast so it wouldnтАЩt damage the train companyтАЩs good name. Hercule started hunting for clues. He found some odd stuff in RichardтАЩs room that seemed a bit off, like a handkerchief with an "H" and a burnt piece of iron that showed a message about revenge. Hercule figured out that Richard had done something really terrible in the past. He had harmed a little girl named Daisy Armstrong, which caused a lot of grief for her whole family. Hercule believed this murder was all about getting back at Richard for what he did to Daisy. As Hercule dug deeper, he discovered that many people on the train had reasons to dislike Richard. There was a big twist when Hercule thought he knew who the killer was, but then someone else got injured! This made the mystery even trickier. 

So, in the end, it turned out that quite a few people on the train had teamed up to plan RichardтАЩs murder as revenge for Daisy. They all had their reasons, all tied back to the sad tale of Daisy Armstrong. Hercule faced a hard choice. He understood why they did it, but he was supposed to uncover the truth. He decided to tell the coppers that a stranger had done it, shielding the folks who actually did it because he felt they had a good reason. And so, Hercule walked away from the case, ready to tell the coppers his version, leaving everyone wowed by his kindness and smarts.

description:
"Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, тАЬIt should not have happenedтАЭ.Would knowing the тАЬWhyтАЭ behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he looks at meтАЭ, тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he/she is behavingтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she is out of his/her mindтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she has gone crazyтАЭ. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. title: Criminal investigation launched into Matthew Perry's death
description:
Law enforcement officials revealed they are launching a criminal investigation into the death of actor Matthew Perry.

Perry was found unresponsive at his Pacific Palisades home on Oct. 28, 2023. Following an autopsy, the Los Angeles County Department of Medical Examiner revealed in December the "Friends" actor died from тАЬacute effects of ketamine.тАЭ

Now, the LAPD tells KTLA 5 News that they're working with the Drug Enforcement Administration and the United States Postal Inspection Service to find out how and why the actor had so much of the substance in his system when he passed away.

KTLA's Sandra Mitchell reports on May 21, 2024.

Details: https://ktla.com/news/local-news/criminal-investigation-launched-into-matthew-perrys-death-over-amounts-of-ketamine-found/

About Crime Patrol :
-----------------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: How Japan's Biggest Murder Investigation Changed the Country Forever
description:
For the residents of the quiet district of Kamisoshigaya, the year 2000 marked the start of changes they never saw coming. From gentrification to the unstoppable expansion of Tokyo, the families living on this once bustling street saw many harsh realities as the times changed, but on the night of December 30th, 2000, at the turn of the year, they would be faced with a murder so gruesome, it would change the landscape of the neighbourhood, and the country, forever.

title: Trump supporters sound off on New York criminal trial
description:
A new CBS News poll shows most people believe Donald Trump is probably guilty of a crime in his New York criminal trial, which will likely go to the jury next week. Trump hosted a rally in the Bronx Thursday night where CBS News campaign reporter Olivia Rinaldi asked supporters of the former president how they felt about the case and its effect on the November election.

Episode 766:  Salma
--------------------------------------------------------
Salma, a 6-year-old who was adored and protected by everyone in her area disappears into thin air one day while coming back from a nearby house. A video of her reading a perfect "Namaaz" at such a young age went viral in her place and was loved by everyone. Police try to find Salma and do everything within their reach but fail but then one day they get a lead which clears everything and reveal the truths that were unimaginable. Watch the episode to know more.

About Crime Patrol : 
----------------------------------------------------
Crime Patrol will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

description:

In today's episode of Crime Patrol, watch the investigation of a kidnapping case from Maharashtra. Two men kidnap a young woman, assuming her to be the daughter of a rich businessman - Mukesh from Mumbai. When the kidnappers call Mukesh for ransom, he refuses to pay the money. Mukesh informs the police about the ransom call when he realizes the seriousness of the case. Will the police be able to solve the case? Stay tuned in to find the answer.
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?'I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Cold Case Collins (24th August 2022)
description:
Former State Pathologist Marie Cassidy will aim to crack the crime of the century.
To mark the centenary of the death of Michael Collins, RT├Й aims to crack one of the biggest unsolved cases in the country.

Cold Case Collins will look to answer the question of what really happened in B├йal na Bl├бth on 22 August 1922, when the renowned Irish revolutionary was killed.

Former State Pathologist Marie Cassidy will host the program, gathering "forensic scientists, criminal investigators, military strategists, archaeologists, archivists and historians" to provide their take on the events leading up to Collins' death.

The experts are set to "sift and filter through the evidence old and new, looking for answers to the questions that have ignited bar brawls for decades."

RT├Й Radio 1's Morning Ireland will broadcast live from the Munster Arms Hotel on Friday, 19 August, where Collins was photographed 30 minutes before the ambush that lead to his death.

Nationwide will also commemorate Collins' death with a series of programs starting from Wednesday, 17 August.

Donal Byrne will look at Collin's early life and influences, before hearing how the young Corkman became a political strategist and organiser.

Michael Collins died during the Irish Civil War, a conflict born out of disagreements over the Anglo-Irish treaty, with Collins supporting the treaty and the Provisional Government.

Prior to his death, he was a prominent political figure in Ireland, having fought in the Easter Rising, before joining the Irish Volunteers and Sinn F├йin.

He was elected as a TD for Cork in 1918, and was made the Minister for Finance in the first organisation of the D├бil.

Nationwide will also commemorate another major anniversary on Monday, 22 August, the 100th anniversary of An Garda S├нoch├бna.

An Garda S├нoch├бna replaced the Royal Irish Constabulary (RIC) and the Dublin Metropolitan Police (DMP) as the primary police force in the country.

Cold Case Collins will air on RT├Й One on Wednesday, 24 August, at 9.35pm

title: Oklahoma's Cold Case Files: Lisa Ledbetter
description:
Lisa Ledbetter was last seen alive around midnight on September 24th, 1984.

Investigators say she and some friends were at a bar near 58th and Peoria.

"She was with a bunch of her friends, and one of them, in addition to his narcotics business and use, was also doing some robberies and burglaries, and in anger, she said, 'I ought to tell the police about you.' We assume that was the motivation for what happened next," says Tulsa County Cold Case Investigator Ed Jackson.

2 News' Sharon Phillips reports. 

Read more at kjrh.com: https://www.kjrh.com/news/local-news/cold-case-files-lisa-ledbetter

title: Cold Case Murder of Kentucky Teen Carol Klaber Solved Nearly 50 Years Later
description:
Sixteen-year-old Carol Sue Klaber left her parent's home in Boone County, Kentucky on June 4, 1976, to go out with a friend after dropping off her bicycle. The next day, she was found dead in a ditch after being sexually assaulted and beaten to death with a tire iron. After nearly 50 years, investigators say they solved the case and identified the killer using DNA technology. The Law&Crime Network's Angenette Levy spoke with cold case detective Coy Cox about the groundbreaking developments in the case and why the investigation continues.

About CID: 
----------------- 
The first thrilling investigative series on Indian Television is today one of the most popular shows on Sony Entertainment Television. Dramatic and absolutely unpredictable, C.I.D. has captivated viewers over the last eleven years and continues to keep audiences glued to their television sets with its thrilling plots and excitement. Also interwoven in its fast-paced plots are the personal challenges that the C.I.D. team faces with non-stop adventure, tremendous pressure, and risk, all in the name of duty. The series consists of hard-core police procedural stories dealing with investigation, detection, and suspense. The protagonists of the serial are an elite group of police officers belonging to the Crime Investigation Department of the police force, led by ACP Pradyuman [played by the dynamic Shivaji Satam]. While the stories are plausible, there is an emphasis on dramatic plotting and technical complexities faced by the police. About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

Caso Beatriz - Confira a entrevista completa com #Lucinha Mota, #m├гe de Beatriz Ang├йlica, morta aos 7 anos de idade, dentro da escola onde estudava, na cidade de Petrolina, em Pernambuco, Brasil. Acompanhe a luta da m├гe e do pai, Sandro Romilton, para que este crime tenha a justi├зa merecida. #CasoBeatriz

https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCDN9trGkW4NiznUCUhHcSmg/join

PLAYLIST COM TODO CONTE├ЪDO BEATRIZ ANG├ЙLICA:

10 de dezembro de 2015 deveria ter sido um grande dia de comemora├з├гo para os Motta da Silva. A primog├кnita da fam├нlia estava se formando no ensino m├йdio, na escola onde ela e seus irm├гos mais novos tamb├йm estudavam, e onde seu pai dava aula de ingl├кs. Entre um evento e outro durante a entrega de diplomas do terceiro colegial, Beatriz Ang├йlica, a ca├зula da turma, avisa a m├гe, Lucinha Mota, que iria at├й o bebedouro tomar ├бgua. Para qualquer pessoa, um pedido absolutamente corriqueiro... E seguro. 

Beatriz estudava no col├йgio, e desde sempre aquele era um local conhecido por toda a fam├нlia. Quinze minutos passam e Lucinha come├зa a estranhar que Beatriz n├гo volta. Se foi o instinto materno que acendeu, ningu├йm sabe, mas imediatamente, mesmo sendo um curto espa├зo de tempo que Beatriz desaparecera, Lucinha j├б come├зa a busca pela filha. O pai de Beatriz, no centro do p├бtio da escola, entregando os diplomas para os alunos, inclusive para sua filha mais velha, ainda n├гo sabe que Beatriz nunca mais seria vista com vida....

Lucinha, os amigos e familiares se espalham pelo grande terreno do col├йgio em busca da menina. Vinte, trinta, quarenta minutos se passam... E nada de Beatriz. Sandro, o pai da menina, ├й avisado que sua ca├зula havia sumido. Ele vai at├й o palco da festa, pega o microfone e chama pela filha. Alguns alunos entram na busca, as pessoas come├зam a procurar pela menina at├й que a pior not├нcia chega at├й Lucinha e Sandro... 

Beatriz havia sido encontrada sem vida. Morta de forma brutal, dentro de uma sala onde dias antes havia tido um inc├кndio criminoso feito por ex-alunos que simplesmente odiavam o local onde haviam estudado. 

Lucinha e Sandro, ainda abalados, n├гo podiam imaginar que aquele seria para sempre o maior divisor de ├бguas de suas vidas. Al├йm de enterrar sua filha mais nova, a doce Beatriz Ang├йlica, o casal teria que se unir ainda mais para conseguir a justi├зa que sua filha merecia ter. Num enredo de cheio de equ├нvocos da pol├нcia civil de Pernambuco, junto com um quase despreparo da per├нcia t├йcnico cientifica da cidade, e ainda a aus├кncia total de solidariedade da escola que foi palco de um crime b├бrbaro, Lucinha e Sandro precisaram encontrar a resili├кncia criada na mais profunda tristeza para n├гo impedirem que perguntas ficassem sem respostas. Perguntas como: Por que tanta maldade com uma crian├зa t├гo pequena? Quem fez isso? H├б um mandante por tr├бs de tudo isso? Qual o nome e o rosto daquele que foi a ├║ltima pessoa a encarar os olhos de Beatriz Ang├йlica?

Depois de seis anos de muita perseveran├зa, chegando a comover o pa├нs inteiro com uma caminhada de mais de 700 quil├┤metros para exigir dos ├│rg├гos competentes que o caso de sua filha tivesse o respeito que qualquer cidad├гo merece ter, os pais de Beatriz conseguem alcan├зar pelo menos um de seus maiores desafios: o autor da morte de sua filha havia sido encontrado. Gra├зas ├а ci├кncia, finalmente, o DNA deixado pelo autor na arma da morte da menina tinha sido cruzado no banco de dados dos criminosos presos no estado de Pernambuco que resultou no nome de Marcelo da Silva, que tem uma longa lista de roubos, furtos e, inclusive, ato sexual contra uma menina de 9 anos de idade.

O DNA entregou Marcelo, que, num primeiro momento, confessou o crime e contou detalhes que somente o autor saberia dizer. Mas... Passados alguns dias j├б como celebridade prisional, Marcelo come├зou a mudar o que disse, colocando em d├║vida se ele seria realmente o algoz de Beatriz. Lucinha e Sandro n├гo t├кm d├║vida, esse ├й o homem que eles procuram desde o dia 10 de dezembro de 2015. E agora, come├зa uma nova e decisiva temporada dessa hist├│ria. 

Beatriz Ang├йlica Mota Ferreira da Silva tinha apenas 7 anos quando foi morta na escola onde estudava, em Petrolina, no estado de Pernambuco, Brasil.

title: The Crime Of Father Amaro
description:
A priest discovers the path of virtue can be steep, and temptation can demand a heavy price, in this controversial drama from Mexico. Father Amaro (Gael Garcia Bernal) is a young Catholic priest whose mentor, the Bishop (Ernesto Gomez Cruz), expects great things from him. However, like all priests, Amaro must first be assigned where he is needed most, which leads him to the small rural community of Los Reyes, where Amaro is to assist Father Benito (Sancho Gracia). To his shock, Amaro discovers Benito is hardly following Holy Law -- he's having an affair with Sanjuanera (Angelica Aragon), a woman who runs a local restaurant, and he's been helping a drug dealer launder his profits in exchange for large donations to the church, which Benito feels is justified as the funds are being used to build a hospital and orphanage for the poor. Amaro is disgusted with Benito's actions, but he soon discovers his own weaknesses when he falls in love with Amelia (Ana Claudia Talancon), Sanjuanera's teenage daughter. As Amelia finds herself falling for Amaro, she breaks off her relationship with Ruben (Andres Montiel), a reporter. Ruben responds by publishing a story which reveals the details of Benito's dealings with the drug dealers; Benito in turn tries to lay the blame at the feet of noble Father Natalio (Damian Alcazar), whose work with local peasants has been wrongly interpreted as supporting armed revolutionary factions. As Amaro tries desperately to distance himself from the growing scandal, he receives shocking news from Amelia when he learns she's pregnant with his child. The Crime of Father Amaro's portrayal of corruption within the Catholic Church led to an outcry from Catholic organizations, both in Mexico and the United States, where they attempted to organize a boycott of the film. However, the tactic failed in Mexico, where the controversy helped to boost ticket sales, making it the highest-grossing Mexican film ever in its native country.

title: Cold Case: Die Medici - Attentat in Florenz Doku (2022)
description:
Die Medici sind die m├дchtigste Familie im Florenz der Renaissance. Sie dominieren Politik und Wirtschaft. Doch ihr Erfolg zieht auch Neider auf sich. Kann die Familie ihre Mitglieder sch├╝tzen?
1478. Italien wird am Beginn der Renaissance von dem folgenschweren Attentat auf den Bankierssohn Giuliano deтАЩ Medici ersch├╝ttert. Florence Kasumba ermittelt mit ihrem Team. Durch die Dechiffrierung geheimer Dokumente k├╢nnen die letzten Mitt├дter enttarnt werden.
Vielen Zeitgenossen ist die Familie Medici mit ihrer Macht ein Dorn im Auge. Die alteingesessene Familie Pazzi will den Einfluss der Medici brechen und plant einen Mordanschlag auf die beiden prominenten Medici-Br├╝der Giuliano und Lorenzo. W├дhrend der Ostermesse 1478 ├╝berf├дllt Francesco deтАЩ Pazzi mit einer Gruppe von M├дnnern die arglosen Br├╝der. Giuliano stirbt sofort unter den w├╝tenden Messerstichen Francescos. Die Brutalit├дt der Tat l├дsst sich an den Gebeinen des Opfers noch heute nachvollziehen. Doch Lorenzo kann entkommen. Der Staatsstreich in Florenz misslingt, weil die B├╝rger gegen├╝ber Lorenzo loyal bleiben. Schnell werden die T├дter gefasst, und die Suche nach den Hinterm├дnnern der Verschw├╢rung beginnt. Das Netz der Verschw├╢rer reicht bis zu Papst Sixtus IV.
Florence Kasumba tr├дgt zusammen mit Historikern wie Marcello Simonetta Hinweise aus Medizin, Psychologie und Kunstgeschichte zusammen. Wer war an der Planung des Anschlags beteiligt? Welche Motive hatten die Verschw├╢rer? In ganz Italien finden die Ermittler geheime Dokumente, die belegen, dass das Attentat mit Billigung des Papstes erfolgte. Marcello Simonetta kann zuletzt nach ├╝ber 500 Jahren mithilfe eines Geheimcodes den milit├дrischen Arm der Verschw├╢rung enttarnen.

About Crime Patrol :
-----------------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Scuba diving attempted murder? Diver Rene Umberger's air ripped from her mouth 50ft underwater
description:
FULL VIDEO HERE: 
http://us.tomonews.net/why-did-someone-rip-this-scuba-diver-rsquo-s-air-supply-from-her-mouth-50-feet-underwater-86848030416896

Check out our official website: http://us.tomonews.net/
Check out our Android app: http://goo.gl/PtT6VD
Check out our iOS app:  http://bit.ly/1gO3z1f

----------------------------------------┬н----------------------------------------┬н----------------

In a video filmed on May 8 by conservationist Rene Umberger off the coast of Kona, Hawaii, two men can be seen collecting fish. When they spot her, one of the men suddenly attacks Umberger and rips her air supply out of her mouth. 

Umberger was swimming at a depth of 50 feet and documenting the state of the reef. 

The two men were collecting reef fish, which is legal under certain circumstances, but when one of the men darted over to Umberger from a great distance and ripped out her regulator, Umberger says it amounted to attempted murder.

Although some divers have a spare regulator to use in case one breaks, many dive without a spare to reduce bulk. For example, the attacker did not have a spare, meaning that if somebody attacked him in the same way, it could be fatal. 

At 50 feet deep, it's not impossible to swim to the surface on one breath, but if the diver has been deep under water for a long time the expansion of accumulated nitrogen in her blood could cause her to suffer "the bends" with possible symptoms ranging from pain to death. Without knowing Umberger's experience level or how long she had already been under water, there was no way the attacker could have safely deprived her of air.

Luckily, Umberger is an experienced diver. She remained calm and was able to put her regulator back in after not breathing for 30 seconds.

Incredibly, the state investigator told Umberger her attacker would be charged, but so would she, for harassment. Umberger is known in Hawaii for her years of advocacy against aquarium fish collection, even where the state has legalized the practice. This has put her at odds with local fishermen who rely on the aquarium industry for a living.

title: Idaho College Murders | A Real Cold Case Detective's Opinion
description:
The murder of four University of Idaho students has rocked the nation. What could be the motive and is there still a threat to the community? 

Lets see what world renowned cold case detective Ken Mains thinks as he dives in the deep waters to get to the truth.

About Ken Mains: You have seen him on the History Channel tracking the Zodiac Killer and on the Discovery Science Channel investigating history's greatest mysteries. Most recently he can be seen on the Reelz Channel giving his expert opinion on the "When Friends Speak" true crime series. 

Detective Mains served a combined 20 years in law enforcement and the United States Marine Corps. You read his best-selling autobiography 'Unsolved No More.' It is said he is "one of this countries greatest detectives" and the foremost authority on unsolved cold cases. He is raw, unfiltered and only cares about the truth. 

The credentials are there: USMC Veteran, Bachelors Degree (Criminal Justice), Masters Degree Studies (Criminal Profiling), Patrol Officer, Undercover Narcotics, FBI Task Force, District Attorney's Office, Drug Task Force Supervisor and Cold Case Detective. He is the founder of AISOCC, where he led the worlds best investigators including the Homicide Hunter Joe Kenda, Dr. Werner Spitz, Dr. Henry Lee, Dr. Mary Ellen O'Toole and Dr. Cyril Wecht, Jim Clemente, Bob Keppel to name a few. Follow renowned Cold Case Expert Ken Mains on his mission to solve the unsolved.

title: Telefacts Crime (17/10/2012): Cold case - Moord op Tania Van Kerkhoven in Berchem
description:
In 1993 stierf Tania Van Kerkhoven uit Edegem bij Antwerpen, op gewelddadige wijze. Ze was pas 17 toen ze van een fuif naar huis reed. Daar is ze nooit aangekomen. De volgende ochtend vind een wandelaar haar lichaam terug in het Brilschanspark in Berchem. Ze is gedood met verschillende messteken. Uit DNA-analyse blijkt dat er mogelijk meerdere daders betrokken waren bij haar dood. Politie en gerecht doen een ultieme oproep naar getuigen om het onderzoek naar deze mysterieuze moord vooruit te helpen.

meer info: http://www.polfed-fedpol.be/dos_ops/vtm/telefacts_crime/2012/TF_crime_17102012_01_nl.php

title: Solving one of Australia's oldest cold case murders | 60 Minutes Australia
description:
In a Brisbane court, one of Australia's most horrendous crimes was finally solved when 78 year-old Vince O'Dempsey was found guilty of murdering young mother Barbara McCulkin and her two daughters, 13 year-old Vicki and 11 year-old Leanne. In all likelihood, the evil thug O'Dempsey will now spend the rest of his life in prison, along with another monster, his 70 year-old co-accused, Garry Dubois, who was convicted of the crime in a separate trial late last year. The murders happened 43 years ago and had been one of Queensland's oldest cold cases.But as Ross Coulthart reports in this major 60 MINUTES investigation, the brutal crime was only solved because of the incredible dedication of two unassuming police detectives who convinced two vital witnesses to do the unthinkable - to break a four-decade-long criminal code of silence (2017).

title: Mystery Surrounds Unsolved Cold Case of Famous Boxer
description: Hector тАЬMachoтАЭ Camacho reigned as a king of the ring in the world of boxing in the 1980s and 1990s. Known for his outlandish costumes, his quick and precise punches, and his bigger than life charisma, тАЬMachoтАЭ skyrocketed from Spanish Harlem to the world stage. But he struggled with drug abuse and trouble with the law, and in 2012, Camacho was shot and killed in Puerto Rico. His murder is still unsolved. description:

description:
TodayтАЩs episode revolves around a mysterious murder case of a young woman in Bhadohi in Uttar Pradesh.  Few villagers have spotted a beheaded dead body of woman and they hurriedly informed the police officials. The killer, in order to hide the identity of the dead body has thrown its head into a river! However, after lot of investigation and search operations the dead body is identified to that of Heena! But, why she is killed? Want to know more? Then stay tuned in the find out here!

Dear Subscriber,
If you are trying to view this video from a location outside India, do note this video will be made available in your territory 48 hours after its upload time 
Click to watch all the episodes of Crime Patrol - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupza0aEZ_FKj0mBguCdtwU_c                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       

Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, тАЬIt should not have happenedтАЭ.Would knowing the тАЬWhyтАЭ behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he looks at meтАЭ, тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he/she is behavingтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she is out of his/her mindтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she has gone crazyтАЭ. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

Zus moordslachtoffer in cold case: 'Heb er alles voor over om iemand te laten praten'
description:
Het opsporingsprogramma Team West besteedt dit jaar aandacht aan zes cold cases uit de regio, waaronder de moord op Maarten Redeker. Zijn zus, Lotty Redeker, vertelt hoe zwaar de moord op haar broer was en hoeveel impact de onopgeloste zaak nu nog heeft op haar leven. Abonneer je hier: https://bit.ly/Omroepwest

Wie zijn wij?
Via het kanaal van Omroep West houden wij je op de hoogte van het laatste nieuws en de meest bijzondere verhalen uit het noordelijke deel van de regio Zuid-Holland (Den Haag, Leiden, Delft, Alphen aan den Rijn en meer). Je bent hier ook aan het juiste adres voor sportnieuws: van kickboksen en amateurvoetbal tot samenvattingen van ADO Den Haag. In het opsporingsprogramma Team West vraagt de politie-eenheid Den Haag jouw hulp bij het oplossen van misdrijven. Daarnaast plaatsen wij mooie documentaires van Westdoc, o.a. over de Schilderswijk, Haagse tradities, Parkpop, vreugdevuren en Golden Earring.

title: SOLVED: 25 Year Old Murder Case | The Abduction of Angie Housman | Cold Case Killers
description:
A 25 year old Cold Case finally solved! On November 18, 1993, Angie Housman disappeared on her way home from school. She was a fourth grader who lived in St. Ann, a quiet suburb of St. Louis, Missouri. She was last seen departing the school bus at her normal bus stop, just eight houses down from her home. After nine days, her frail body was found tied to a tree by a deer hunter in the Busch Wildlife Conservation Area in St. Charles County, a remote area near St. Louis.

On January 30, 2008, at around 7.30 a.m., a motorist called 911 to report the discovery of a dead body on the side of Interstate 540 in North Carolina. When police located the body, it was identified as 21-year-old University student Latrese Curtis. Her car was discovered just a few miles away. What had happened to her? description:

Today's episode continues with the search of AshishтАЩs murderer. Yusuf and Nabir admit before police that they are pickpockets. While investigating the case, the police find out that AshishтАЩs friends had planned to kill him. Will the police be able to find the murderer? Stay tuned in to find the answer.
Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?'I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: 9 Shocking Moments in Christopher Gregor's Child Murder Trial: 'Not One Scintilla!'
description:
Christopher Gregor, 31, is on trial for the murder of his 6-year-old son, Corey Micciolo, on April 2, 2021. Gregor's defense has argued that he is innocent and has cast blame on Corey's mother for his death. During the second week of Gregor's trial, a nurse who cared for Corey in the hospital testified along with an Ocean County sheriff's detective, a child abuse hotline screener and a forensic pathologist. Gregor's parents also testified in a hearing where the jury wasn't present. Law&Crime's Angenette Levy goes through the biggest moments in the testimony from the week in this episode of Crime Fix тАФ a daily show covering the biggest stories in crime.

About Crime Patrol :
-----------------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Cold Case - Tia Joe
description:
Welcome to "Crime and Justice," where we delve into perplexing cold cases that continue to haunt communities. In this episode, we unravel the tragic events surrounding the unsolved murder of Tia Lanae Joe Bennett, a 21-year-old woman who was ruthlessly gunned down in her Novi, Michigan home on April 7, 2019.

As we explore the chilling details of this heinous crime, we uncover the heart-wrenching truth that Tia's six-month-old son was also a victim but miraculously survived his injuries. This shocking murder has since been classified as Novi's fourth cold case, leaving the Novi Police Department grasping for answers.

Join us as we bring attention to this unresolved tragedy, shedding light on the diligent efforts made by law enforcement to crack this perplexing case. As the years pass, the investigation continues, and we call upon the public to share any information that may bring justice to Tia and her surviving loved ones.

Watch this gripping video as we delve into the known facts, untangle the web of mysteries, and explore the potential leads in this Novi cold case. Subscribe to "Crime and Justice" and become part of the collective effort to seek truth and resolution in unsolved crimes.

About the show:
--------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: ╪н┘Д ┘Е╪┤┘Г┘Д╪й ╪з┘Д┘Б╪╡┘Д╪й ╪з┘И ╪з╪о╪к┘Б╪з╪б ╪з╪┤╪з╪▒╪й ╪з┘Д╪▒╪з╪к╪▒
Crime Patrol Dastak - False Pride - Episode 344 - 1st March 2014
description:
Ep 344 - Crime Patrol: Dastak: Bhinderpal Chaudhary residing in Bhoira Village located in Haryana was extremely upset as he lost his Daughter-in-law and new born Son. Bhinderpal's Son Hukum Chaudhary didn't marry since then. One of the Villagers residing in Amar's Village comes across Devika and also talks about her marriage with Amar's Brother Shyam. Bhinderpal offers a deal to Amar. Smriti is been forced to settle down with Hukum. Will Smriti land in deep trouble? To know more, watch this thrilling episode.


"Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, "It should not have happened".Would knowing the "Why" behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?"I don't like the way he looks at me", "I don't like the way he/she is behaving", "I think he/she is out of his/her mind", "I think he/she has gone crazy". That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.Feelings... expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting."For more information on your favourite show do visit

www.facebook.com/SonyLiv  and follow us on 
www.twitter.com/SonyLiv""

title: Agression de Dieudonn├й
description:
Le tribunal correctionnel de Fort-de-France a condamn├й samedi matin ├а 6 mois de prison dont 1 mois ferme et ├а un euro symbolique de dommages et int├йr├кts, les quatre agresseurs de Dieudonn├й, au terme de 12 heures de d├йbat.

Les pr├йvenus ├йtaient poursuivis pour ┬л violences en r├йunion avec pr├йm├йditation ┬╗ apr├иs l'agression de l'humoriste, le 1er mars dernier, sur le parking d'Antilles T├йl├йvision (ATV) ├а Fort-de-France.

Au cours de l'audience ouverte vendredi ├а 14 heures (19 h ├а Paris), les avocats de Dieudonn├й ont tent├й en vain de faire retenir la qualification d'injures raciales puisque l'humoriste s'├йtait fait traiter de ┬л sale n├йgro ┬╗ avant d'├кtre frapp├й par ses agresseurs.

Dans son r├йquisitoire, le procureur de la r├йpublique avait retenu les injures raciales et r├йclam├й une peine de 6 mois de prison dont trois ferme. De toute ├йvidence, sous la pression politique, le juge n'a pas retenu la th├иse des injures raciales.

A l'appel de plusieurs organisations associatives et politiques, plus de mille personnes s'├йtaient r├йunies devant le palais de justice, durant le proc├иs. A l'├йnonc├й du jugement, de vives r├йactions d'hostilit├йs se sont exprim├йes dans la foule.

description:
#CasoIzadora - Entrevista com a advogada de defesa m├гe e irm├гo de Izadora, Dra Esmaela Mac├кdo. Izadora Santos Mour├гo tinha apenas 41 anos quando foi morta a facadas no dia 13 de fevereiro de 2021, no munic├нpio de Pedro II, no estado do Piau├н. Advogada, Izadora estava na casa de sua m├гe, Maria Nerci, quando o crime aconteceu. Dormindo no quarto do #irm├гo, Izadora teria sido encontrada j├б sem vida pela #m├гe e por uma funcion├бria da casa. Como um quebra cabe├зas que faltam pe├зas e outras n├гo encaixam muito bem, a pol├нcia logo chega ├а motiva├з├гo e aos autores do crime... Uma #heran├зa de 4 milh├╡es de reais teria sido o porqu├к da morte de Izadora, j├б a autoria, segundo a pol├нcia e o minist├йrio p├║blico, seria de sua m├гe e de seu irm├гo, Jo├гo Paulo Mour├гo. 

Num primeiro momento, ambos negaram que tivessem cometido o assassinato daquela que chamavam de filha e irm├г. Alguns dias depois, a m├гe assumiu o crime sozinha, descartando a participa├з├гo de seu filho... A pol├нcia e a promotoria mantiveram m├гe e filho como os respons├бveis pelas facadas em Izadora. No entanto, no julgamento do dia 16 de mar├зo de 2022, Maria Nerci foi condenada a 19 anos e 6 meses de pris├гo. J├б o irm├гo Jo├гo Paulo foi inocentado.

description:

On September 19th of 2021, UK law enforcement received notice of an incredibly terrifying situation. A man from Derbyshire had called the emergency line to report something horrific. His voice was eerily calm as he broke the disturbing news. . 

Paramedics and cops rushed to the scene. They quickly found 33 year old Damien Bendall standing outside of his home. There was some blood on his clothes and he admitted to the paramedics that he had hurt himself physically by using a weapon he got from the kitchen of the home. 

At first, law enforcement seemed to think that Damien was having a psychotic break but hadnтАЩt actually hurt anyone, just thought he did. They would soon change their minds when they took a look at the horror-like scene inside of the home.

title: ┬л Attrape-laтАп! ┬╗ : Caroline Margeridon livre de nouveaux d├йtails gla├зants sur son agression
description:
┬л Attrape-laтАп! ┬╗ : Caroline Margeridon livre de nouveaux d├йtails gla├зants sur son agression
Quelques semaines apr├иs son agression sur un parking de Saint-Ouen, Caroline Margeridon ├йtait de passage sur les ondes de RTL, dans l'├йmission On refait la t├йl├й. Elle a accept├й de revenir sur l'incident, qui a fait une belle frayeur ├а ses fans.

L'ann├йe 2023 a tr├иs mal d├йbut├й pour Caroline Margeridon. Le 8 janvier dernier, le journal 20 Minutes r├йv├йlait que la c├йl├иbre acheteuse de l'├йmission Affaire Conclue avait ├йt├й agress├йe. Cette derni├иre a port├й plainte apr├иs avoir ├йt├й frapp├йe et vol├йe par deux hommes ├а Saint-Ouen, en Seine-Saint-Denis, alors qu'elle s'appr├кtait ├а monter dans sa voiture. La collectionneuse ├йtait gar├йe pr├иs du march├й Biron, dans les puces de Saint-Ouen, o├╣ elle poss├иde une boutique tr├иs fr├йquent├йe. L'un des deux individus "lтАЩa attrap├йe par-derri├иre et lui a mis la main sur la bouche pour lтАЩemp├кcher de crier", pendant que son complice lui a arrach├й sa montre et son sac de luxe. Si la montre n'avait pas grande valeur, le sac, lui, valait plus de 10 000 euros.

La nouvelle de son agression avait ├йvidemment alert├й ses fans, qui attendaient avec impatience que cette derni├иre donne de ses nouvelles. C'est ce qu'elle a fait d├иs le lendemain soir gr├вce ├а une vid├йo publi├йe sur Instagram, o├╣ elle est apparue aux c├┤t├йs de sa fille Victoire. "Bien s├╗r qu'il faut toujours faire attention, mais je fais toujours attention. Je ne vais jamais dans ce parking, seule. Jamais ! Cela fait des ann├йes que je suis aux Puces, des ann├йes que je vais au March├й Biron. J'y vais toujours accompagn├йe de mes amis ou ils vont chercher ma voiture. Bon, c'est la vie. On n'est pas mortes", avait-elle relativis├й.


Caroline Margeridon choqu├йe par la vid├йo de son agression
Plusieurs semaines apr├иs les faits, Caroline Margeridon a accept├й de revenir sur cet incident lors de son passage dans l'├йmission de RTL On refait la t├йl├й, ce samedi 28 janvier. Si elle dit n'avoir pas ├йt├й traumatis├йe par son agression, elle ne cache pas avoir ├йt├й beaucoup plus choqu├йe lorsque la police lui a montr├й une vid├йo des faits, prise gr├вce aux cam├йras de vid├йo surveillance. "L├а, jтАЩai vu mon agression. CтАЩest vrai que je me suis retrouv├йe avec un ┼Уil au beurre noir assez costaud et des bleus partout alors que je nтАЩavais rien senti. CтАЩest assez traumatisant de se voir", a-t-elle conc├йd├й.

Autre fait qui l'a marqu├йe : la mani├иre dont les deux individus se sont approch├йs d'elle. "Ce qui mтАЩa fait flipper, cтАЩest que jтАЩentends dтАЩabord 'courir' au moment o├╣ jтАЩouvre ma porti├иre, et jтАЩentends 'attrape-la'. Ils ont enfonc├й leurs grosses mains dans mon ┼Уil et ils ont appuy├й tellement fort que ├зa mтАЩa fait un h├йmatome", a expliqu├й Caroline Margeridon. Heureusement il ne s'agit que d'un mauvais souvenir pour la collectionneuse, qui a bon espoir de voir les malfaiteurs appr├йhend├йs par la police.

title: Cold Case Solved 42 years later-Phoenix Police Department
description:
The Phoenix Police Department arrested a man wanted in a murder and sexual assault that happened more than four decades ago.

Glenn Williams was arrested April 9, 2020 for a crime committed on June 10, 1978.
At the time, Phoenix Police found Fernando Calleros and a woman in the bed of a pickup truck in the area of 32nd street and Broadway. 23-year-old Calleros had been beaten to death while the woman was beaten and had been sexually assaulted.  She survived the attack.  

Evidence was collected, processed and in January 1979, Williams was taken into custody.  He was interviewed by detectives and despite denying involvement, he was booked into jail and charged with the crime.  

The charges were eventually тАЬturned downтАЭ due to a lack of evidence and Williams was released from jail.  Detectives had done all they could and exhausted all the technology available to them at that time.

In 2019, the case was reexamined by the Phoenix Police Department Cold Case Homicide Squad. Thanks to advances in technology, they were able to link Williams to the crime and arrest him on first degree murder and sexual assault charges.

title: Criminal Law
description: After obtaining an acquittal in a murder trial, criminal defense attorney Ben Chase (Gary Oldman) decides to prove that his client Martin Thiel (Kevin Bacon) is in fact a serial killer. When new murders occur, Ben takes matters into his own hands, beginning a psychological battle of wills with Martin. Gary Oldman gives an excellent performance as the criminal defense attorney with a conscience, and Kevin Bacon is intriguing and ambiguous as the killer. The action sequences -- particularly when Ben finds a body in the rain in a deserted park -- are terrific as is the fast-paced direction by Martin Campbell.

MISSING: Melissa Highsmith (Solved Cold Case)

Missing person cases rarely have a happy ending - but that isnтАЩt true in the case of Melissa Highsmith, a woman who went missing back in 1971 and was finally located in 2022. Melissa was stolen from her home when she was only 1-year-old, stolen by a woman who claimed to be her babysitter. The Highsmith family had only recently moved into their new home in Texas when MelissaтАЩs mother placed an ad in the paper looking for a babysitter. 

MelissaтАЩs mother hired a woman who responded to the ad, with the babysitter picking the infant up on the afternoon of August 23rd. This was the last time Melissa was seen for decades. 

As it would turn out, Melissa was finally found after sheтАЩd taken part in a 23andMe test - having no idea that sheтАЩd been missing for all these years. When the results came in, the family was reunited soon after.

title: Wedding DJ Arrested for 25-Year-Old Cold Case Killing of Teacher: Cops
description: Police in Lancaster, Pennsylvania say they arrested a popular wedding DJ in connection with a cold case killing from 1992. 25-year-old Christy Mirack was found sexually assaulted, beaten and strangled in her home. Authorities say DNA evidence found at the scene recently matched a sample in a public genealogy database that led them to 49-year-old Raymond Rowe, a popular wedding disc jockey known as DJ Freez. About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: 40-Year-Old Cold Case FINALLY Solved | Dawn Olanick's Cold Case!
description:
40-Year-Old Cold Case Solved | Dawn Olanick's Cold Case!

Forty years ago, the dead body of a teenage girl was found in a cemetery in the state of New Jersey. The case captured national headlines for years afterward.
That was Princess Doe, the first dead body to go on the records at the National Crime Information Center as an unidentified victim of a gruesome murder.
It took all this time for her identity to be revealed. Her killer has now been found.
So who was Princess Doe, and how did she die? Watch our episode to find out. And like, share, and subscribe to stay updated with all the most recent and stunning developments that help to resolve cold cases of homicide from the past.

title: Man arrested in murder of pregnant Amish woman found dead in her Pennsylvania home
description:
Police have announced an arrest in connection to the death of 23-year-old pregnant Rebekah A. Byler that has shaken an Amish community in rural Pennsylvania.

The Pennsylvania State Police announced early Saturday morning that Shawn Cranston -- a 52-year-old man from Corry, Pennsylvania -- has been arrested in connection with the murder of the Amish woman and is now facing multiple charges, including criminal homicide, criminal homicide of an unborn child, burglary and criminal trespass.

Cranston was arraigned Saturday morning and is currently being held without bond at the Crawford County Jail.
