title: Agression rwandaise: suivez la suite des actualit├йs s├йcuritaires et politiques de c vendredi 24/5/24
description:
Agression rwandaise/M23 : suivez la suite des actualit├йs s├йcuritaires et politiques de ce vendredi 24/5/24


La plus grande erreur de Kagame est de rester fig├й dans la gloire du pass├й sans s'adapter aux nouvelles r├йalit├йs. Certaines choses ne se comprennent qu'en les explorant davantage. Kagame ne va pas l├вcher la RDC car les v├йritables enjeux sont les ressources comme le coltan et d'autres minerais pr├йcieux.
Avec les avanc├йes des FARDC et des Wazalendo, il cherchera probablement ├а lancer une offensive pour prendre une grande ville comme Sake ou Goma, afin de faire plier Tshisekedi. Ce serait une grave erreur, car il y perdra de nombreux ├йl├йments. Ensuite, Kagame sera contraint de tirer sur sa propre population pour pr├йtendre que les FARDC l'ont attaqu├й et ainsi d├йclarer la guerre.
Mais cela sera un ├йchec. Qui vivra verra. Cette guerre est la derni├иre. Jamais dans l'histoire des conflits depuis 1996, le Rwanda et l'Ouganda n'ont perdu autant d'hommes en RDC. Kagame pensait mener une guerre de cinq jours pour faire plier Tshisekedi.
Il a oubli├й que Tshisekedi n'est pas comme l'ancien pr├йsident. Avec la tournure des ├йv├йnements, soit les terroristes du M23 capituleront et un dialogue s'ouvrira entre la RDC et le Rwanda, avec le Rwanda en position de faiblesse, soit ce sera la guerre totale.
Nous atteindrons un point o├╣ les hommes de Makanika se rendront d'eux-m├кmes...
Apr├иs la guerre, la RDC a document├й toutes les exactions commises par le M23. Ces actes seront attribu├йs individuellement aux hommes et femmes qui ont rejoint le M23, comme Corbeille Nangaa, Chalwe, Henry Magie, et des mandats d'arr├кt internationaux seront ├йmis contre eux.

Des rudes affrontements opposent depuis le matin de ce vendredi 24 mai 2024, les rebelles du M23 aux forces arm├йes de la R├йpublique d├йmocratique du Congo (FARDC), appuy├йes par les volontaires pour la d├йfense de la patrie (VDP), appel├йs aussi ┬л wazalendo ┬╗, dans lтАЩagglom├йration de Mulimbi, groupement de Tongo, dans la chefferie de Bwito (territoire de Rutshuru). Selon la soci├йt├й civile locale, ce sont les wazalendo qui ont lanc├й l'assaut contre les positions du M23 en vue de tenter de les d├йloger de Mulimbi.  ┬л Des d├йtonations en armes lourdes et l├йg├иres se font entendre partout dans lтАЩagglom├йration de Mulimbi. Les wazalendo ont surpris les rebelles du M23 en les attaquant de partout ├а Mulimbi. Les habitants sont terr├йs chez eux. Nous craignons qu'il y ait des massacres de civils si les wazalendo d├йcrochaient. Nous les encourageons donc ├а d├йloger l'ennemi de Mulimbi et de partout ailleurs ┬╗, a indiqu├й une source de la soci├йt├й civile locale.  Combats M23_RDF_Wazalendo_FARDC : apr├иs la prise de la colline de Ndumba cette semaine en territoire de Masisi dans la chefferie de Bahunde, l'arm├йe congolaise encercle le village de Kiluku dernier verrou pour la cit├й de Shasha sur la route Sake Minova. Contrairement ├а ce que disent plusieurs publications dont " la Radio OKAPI" la cit├й de Shasha reste sous contr├┤le de la coalition M23_RDF_AFC. Shasha est une cit├й qui est au bord du lac Kivu sur la route Sake Minova. Sa partie ouest (Kituva, Ndumba, Kiluku sont des collines. Les FARDC sont donc dans les collines et la coalition M23_RDF_AFC est dans la vall├йe. Une grande partie de la population de cette chefferie de Bahunde a quitt├й ce village. "Je suis dans la cit├й de Shasha, il est structement interdit ici de filmer mais je suis ├а quelques m├иtres du Bureau que le M23 a install├й dans la cit├й ├а l'h├┤pital de Shasha, quelques ├йl├йments sont l├а maintenant et d'autres dans leurs positions mais pas vraiment nombreux. Les FARDC sont sur la colline de Ndumba et mon fils qui est ├а Kiluku m'a dit que les Wazalendo encerclent le village de Kiluku", a d├йclar├й un habitant dont je ne cite pas le nom en raison notamment de sa s├йcurit├й. Hier Jeudi, 3 bombes ont vis├й la cit├й de Minova dans le sud Kivu. Des experts militaires ont pr├йcis├й que ces bombes provenaient des zones M23.
RDC, ELLE FONT LA FIERT├Й DE LA FEMME CONGOLAISE, elles ont d├йcid├й de D├йfendre toute une Nation, de se battre pour la Lib├йration du Pays. Elles ├йtaient Aussi Pr├йsente ├а SHASHA. Rappelons que Les FARDC recrutent les Filles de 18 ├а 25 ans. 

le pr├йsident Biden  a annonc├й son intention de d├йsigner le Kenya  StateHouseKenya comme un alli├й majeur des ├Йtats-Unis non-OTAN, la premi├иre d├йsignation de ce type pour un sous-marin -Pays d'Afrique saharienne. Le Kenya deviendra le premier pays subsaharien ├а recevoir cette d├йsignation, ce qui permettra au pays b├йn├йficiaire d'obtenir des armes plus sophistiqu├йes aupr├иs des ├Йtats-Unis et de s'engager dans une coop├йration plus ├йtroite en mati├иre de s├йcurit├й.  j'ai r├йcemment d├йp├кch├й mon ministre des affaires ├йtrang├иres ├а Kinshasa, et d'ici peu, nous allons voir comment commencer le dialogue sous le processus de Nairobi. Nous croyons qu'il n'y a pas de solution militaire dans l'est de la RDC", d├йclare le pr├йsident  @WilliamsRuto

title: Crime Patrol - Gauri Disagrees To Stay With Ratan Prakash & Saroj Mishra - Episode 131 - 15th July 2012
description:
Bua use to behave rude with Gauri and also forced her to do all the house hold work at such a tender age later, she was not allowed to talk to their 2 son and use to always keep her away from studies. Pinto reveals Gauri that her Mother will never ever return back. On the other side, Ratan Mishra reveals his family members that they have decided to adopt Gauri and his family members agree too, there in the jail, Gauri reveals Vijay that she got arrested by police for stealing Bua's Gold jewellery which was actually a full proof plan of Bua, just to remove her from the house and thus she was send to 'Juvenile Home' for the crime that she never committed. Vijay reveals Jailer that she has strictly disagreed to go with Mr. Mishra but has agreed to meet them once, later, Gauri gets emotional as Ratan and Saroj reveals them that they do not require a maid but a Daughter with whom they can spend their rest of the life happily and also assures her that they will help her in fulfilling her dream too. What will be Gauri's final decision? Will she accept Ratan and Saroj as her Parents?
Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, "It should not have happened".Would knowing the "Why" behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?"I don't like the way he looks at me", "I don't like the way he/she is behaving", "I think he/she is out of his/her mind", "I think he/she has gone crazy". That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.Feelings... expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

description:

Nazneen is in a relationship with Dheeraj when her marriage is fixed with Ashraf. Nazeen, wants to be with Dheeraj, but is forced to tie the knot with Ashraf. Even after marriage the relationship between Nazneen and Dheeraj does not fade away. Will Nazneen take an extreme step to live with Dheeraj? Watch this episode to find out.

#crimepatrol #рдХреНрд░рд╛рдЗрдордкреЗрдЯреНрд░реЛрд▓ #setindia #рдХреНрд░рд╛рдЗрдордкрдЯреНрд░реЛрд▓рд╕рддрд░реНрдХ #crimepatrolsatark #crimepatrol #crime #thrillers #CP #рдХреНрд░рд╛рдЗрдордкреИрдЯреНрд░реЙрд▓рд╕рддрд░реНрдХ #livcrime #crimepatroldastak #crimepatroldial100 #anupsoni #crimepatrolsatark #crimepatrolfullepisode #crimepatrollatestepisode #crimepatrolnewepisode #crimepatroldial100 #crimepatrol2024 #crimepatrolserial #crimepatrolbestepisode #crimepatrolsony #crimepatrolnewepisode #bestcrimepatrolepisode #crimepatrolmostpopularepisode #рдХреНрд░рд╛рдЗрдордкреЗрдЯреНрд░реЛрд▓ #crimepatrolcases #crimeworld #crimeworld2024 #crimeworldnewepisode #crimeworldbestepisode #crimeworldfullepisode #indiancrime #indiancrimestories

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: TRUE CRIME: Rache in der Familie - Eine Analyse der Ermittlung | Dem T├дter auf der Spur S1E02 | WELT
description:
TRUE CRIME: Rache in der Familie - Eine Analyse der Ermittlung | Dem T├дter auf der Spur S1E02 | WELT 
Der 30-j├дhrige Andrew Scanlan wird als vermisst gemeldet. Unklare Zeugenaussagen schicken die Polizei zun├дchst auf eine falsche F├дhrte, bis ein Augenzeugenbericht klarstellt, dass Andrew an dem Abend, an dem er zuletzt gesehen wurde, mit seinen beiden Halbbr├╝dern zusammen war.

In den fr├╝hen Morgenstunden des 22. November 2006 verschwindet Andrew Scanlan spurlos, ein Ereignis, das f├╝r einen Strudel aus Verd├дchtigungen, Geheimnissen und letztlich einer tragischen Entdeckung sorgt. Andrew, bekannt f├╝r seine sporadischen Konflikte mit dem Gesetz und seine K├дmpfe mit der Heroinabh├дngigkeit, verl├дsst eines Nachts unerwartet das sichere Ufer seines gewohnten Lebens, getrieben von der Aussicht auf ein unerwartetes Erbe, das ihn in die Arme seines eigenen Verderbens f├╝hrt.

Die Ermittlung, gef├╝hrt von einem erfahrenen Detektiv, der seine Karriere dem Aufkl├дren dunkler Geheimnisse gewidmet hat, st├╢├Яt schnell auf ein Gewirr aus L├╝gen und T├дuschungen. Anfangs f├╝hren alle Spuren ins Leere, und die Personen, die Andrew zuletzt lebend gesehen haben, schweigen oder verwischen die Spuren. Doch die Hartn├дckigkeit und das unerm├╝dliche Bem├╝hen des Ermittlerteams, unterst├╝tzt durch forensische Technologien und Zeugenaussagen, enth├╝llen schlie├Яlich eine Geschichte von Rache und Verrat, tief verwurzelt in den vergangenen Taten und unausgesprochenen Feindseligkeiten innerhalb einer zerr├╝tteten Familie.

Diese Doku zeichnet die komplexen Wendungen des Falls nach, von Andrews pl├╢tzlichem Verschwinden ├╝ber die chaotischen Anf├дnge der Ermittlung bis hin zur grausamen Wahrheit, die unter einem unscheinbaren Erdh├╝gel verborgen lag. Es ist eine Geschichte, die nicht nur das dunkle Potenzial menschlicher Emotionen und die Abgr├╝nde zwischenmenschlicher Beziehungen aufzeigt, sondern auch die unerm├╝dliche Entschlossenheit derjenigen beleuchtet, die der Gerechtigkeit dienen.

title: р┤ор╡Вр┤ир╡Нр┤ир┤┐р┤▓р╡Кр┤ир╡Нр┤ир╡НтАМ | Malayalam Full Movie Monnilonnu | Crime Thriller | Ashokan
description:
This is a #Malayalam #Full #Movie #Moonilonnu (#1994). #Starring  #Ashokan , #Valsala #Menon , #Kukku #Parameswaran , #Jagannatha #Varma , #Ramachandran & others.

Movie Synopsis
-----------------------
Moonilonnu (1994) is a malayalam crime thriller. Directed by Haridas. Starring Ashokan ,Valsala Menon ,Kukku Parameswaran ,Jagannatha Varma ,Ramachandran & others. Moonnilonnu says about a crime story of distorted love. This seems to be partly because people have a hard time being completely honest, even when surveyed in ways that safeguard their anonymity. ThereтАЩs still some shame and guilt associated with admitting the truth, even in private. So instead of sharing a bunch of detailed stats that might be wrong, IтАЩll simply share the big picture elements.Slightly more than half of all married people will cheat on their spouses at some point in their lives. 

Men apparently cheat more often than women, but the gap isnтАЩt huge.Most of the time cheating does occur, the other spouse doesnтАЩt know it, with women being in the dark slightly more often than men. ThatтАЩs if youтАЩre married. If youтАЩre in a committed relationship but arenтАЩt married, then IтАЩd imagine that the odds of cheating are even higher. Partly I say that because cheating is more common when youтАЩre younger and becomes less likely as you age.In this modern world the ration of cheaters vs sincere ones are getting big difference. Many people are now getting into love affairs for the sake of money. Love is almost a third party emotion now. Love is now turned into more objective than subjective.
                       
In this movie we can see a parallel love affair. A bachelor called Gopi, who is from a poor family deliberately gets into love affairs with women. Three woman are Ambili, kalyani & Chandrika. Three woman were sisters and was from a higher family. Ambi was the youngest and was a college student. Chandrika was also  college student. Kalyani was a government employee. Their father was a busy business man and a widower. Gopi was a crooked guy, he tacticaly traped  Ambily. She was so innocent girl. She gave everything she had to him. She trusted him a lot. But Gopi's intention was something else. 

Which is unknown throughout the story. Gopu behaved like a vampire to her. When he came to know that she is carrying, he murdered her tactically from a hilltop and he vanished from the spot. The case went on with no evidence, and almost got into as a suicide. Vijayan who is the nefew of her, felt suspicious in her death. He started his personal enquiry. He gone through her college and her hostler mates. On the other hand Chandrika was also in the same pursuit. 

Vijayan found that her suicide is a planned murder. Meanwhile Chandrika got a bit more closer to the suspect. Before she could unmask him, Gopi came to hear about it; and he killed her is a planned accident. The other part is, he was already in gilted love with her. But unfortunately she didn't know about his jilted love. On the other hand Vijayan tightened his enquiry. Now Gopi is behind Kalyani. He tactically nailed her attention followed by her love. her so called "lover" so clever in planning things. 

He impressed Kalyani's father with his flattery words and managed to acquire the administration of their estate. At last Vijayan hooked the culprit, but there was not much evidences with him to prove it. The date of Kalyani & Gopi's mariage got declared. And now the movie is going to have a thrilling climax. So will Gopi get the ultimate punishment from destiny? Can Vijayan stop him from next murder? Watch full movie "Moonilonnu"

Writer -  Dr Haridas
Starring - Ashokan ,Valsala Menon ,Kukku Parameswaran ,Jagannatha Varma ,Ramachandran & others.

About The CID :
The first thrilling investigative series on Indian Television is today one of the most popular shows.  Dramatic and absolutely unpredictable, C.I.D. has captivated viewers over the last eleven years and continues to keep audiences glued to their television sets with its thrilling plots and excitement. Also interwoven in its fast-paced plots are the personal challenges that the C.I.D. team faces with non-stop adventure, tremendous pressure, and risk, all in the name of duty. The series consists of hard-core police procedural stories dealing with investigation, detection, and suspense. The protagonists of the serial are an elite group of police officers belonging to the Crime Investigation Department of the police force, led by ACP Pradyuman, played by the dynamic Shivaji Satam along with Daya and Abhijit. While the stories are plausible, there is an emphasis on dramatic plotting and technical complexities faced by the police. At every stage, the plot throws up intriguing twists and turns to keep the officers on the move as they track criminals, led by the smallest of clues.

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

The INSANE TWISTED 1985 Cold Case FINALLY Solved In 2022 I Cold Case Files
===============================================================================

On July 17th, 1985, 29-year-old Benny Scruggs was found stabbed in the chest in his caravan in Travis Drive, Wisconsin. The stab was from a large knife that had severed his lung. Benny was already dead when the police arrived. There were no initial suspects in the case, however, things took a turn, when slowly BennyтАЩs wife, Yvonne, started becoming the centre of the case. The case took 37 years to reach a conclusion, and finally in 2022, the cold case entered its climax.

title: Coldcase: Koos Engel - 21 januari 2012
description:
Coldcase: Koos Engel
doodgestoken

21 januari 2012
Tuitjenhorn - Noord-Holland

Oproep: Rosan, zus van Koos


Wat is er gebeurd?

Op 21 januari 2012 werd Koos Engel (43) neergestoken voor zijn caf├й Los Amiquitos in Tuitjenhorn. Rond 3.15 uur liep Koos naar buiten, waarschijnlijk om een ruzie te sussen dat zich voor het caf├й afspeelde. Hij werd neergestoken en liep terug naar het caf├й, daar waren zijn collegaтАЩs die hem direct te hulp schoten. De politie heeft vrij snel vier mannen aangehouden, zij werden echter ook weer vrijgelaten omdat uit onderzoek niet vastgesteld kon worden dat zij betrokken waren bij de dodelijke steek. Later zijn nog eens drie mannen aangehouden, maar ook zij zijn vrijgelaten vanwege onvoldoende bewijs. Tot op de dag van vandaag is nog steeds onbekend wie Koos heeft doodgestoken.

Wie was Koos?

Na een lange vakantie in Venezuela besloot Koos naar dit land te emigreren en hij heeft daar vijftien jaar gewoond. Hij leerde hier zijn toenmalige vriendin kennen met wie hij een dochter, Rosanna, kreeg. Rosanna is o.a. vernoemd naar de zus van Koos, Rosan. Koos leerde in Venezuela ook zijn compagnon kennen met wie hij in 2008 caf├й Los Amiquitos opende in Nederland in Tuitjenhorn.
Kort na het vertrek van Koos naar Nederland is zijn dochter Rosanna met haar moeder verhuisd naar Mexico en daar wonen zij nog steeds. Ondanks de grote afstand hadden Koos en Rosanna een hechte band. Rosanna heeft haar zoontje vernoemd naar haar vader Koos. Koos wordt door zijn zus Rosan omschreven als een тАШenorme goedzakтАЩ en hun band als тАШtwee zielen ├й├йn gedachteтАЩ.

Hoe staat de zaak ervoor?

In 2018 verscheen de zaak in Opsporing Verzocht. Daar werd vermeld dat zich een getuige bij de politie had gemeld. Helaas heeft dit niet geleid tot meer duidelijkheid wie er verantwoordelijk is voor de dood op Koos.

Familie

Rosan, de zus van Koos, is ervan overtuigd dat degene die Koos heeft gestoken niet het doel had om hem om het leven te brengen. Ze gaat er ook vanuit dat er getuigen moeten zijn geweest van het incident, omdat er tijdens het gevecht veel mensen op straat waren. Rosan hoopt dat diegene nu opstaat: тАШLaat het gewoon weten, want wij kunnen nu niet door, wij kunnen niets afsluiten.тАЩ

title: The Gandhi Murder
description: This is a movie based on real events that shaped India as a secular, democratic country, and paved the way for the world's largest democracy, as it struggled and survived through its formative days immediately after independence from the British Empire. The movie draws an interesting parallel between India during the life and assassination of Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi, and the U.S. during the life and assassination of Abraham Lincoln, and how their eventual assassinations, though tragic events in themselves, virtually turned the two countries around to be successful secular democracies, from the separatist and civil war path on which both were trudging.

title: Bystanders stop robber at Australian liquor store
description:
A man was arrested after he attempted to rob a liquor store in Australia last month. Surveillance footage shows the suspect threatening the shopkeeper and trying to steal the cash register before nearby bystanders stepped in to stop him.

The suspect fled, but was located two weeks later and charged with aggravated robbery and assault, police said.

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Agression rwandaise : suivez la suite des actualit├йs s├йcuritaires et politique de ce mardi 28/5/24
description:
Agression rwandaise : suivez la suite des actualit├йs s├йcuritaires et politique de ce mardi 28/5/24

Dans la journ├йe de ce Lundi 27 Mai, Nos L├йopards FARDC et Les R├йsistants Patriotes Congolais ЁЯЗиЁЯЗй de l'Auto-D├йfense #WAZALENDO ont fait une perc├йe remarquable aux environs de Kiwanja ├а Kahunga...   De l'autre c├┤t├й ├а KABINDI pr├иs de BUNAGANA, des Tirs ├а Armes Lourdes et L├йg├иres ont ├йt├й entendus.  la Guerre est Tellement compliqu├йe au Point que les terroristes Rwandais RDF ne comprennent Rien.  Nous rappelons Toujours que les Gens doivent savoir que cette Guerre sera gagn├йe par la #RDC   
Les FARDC accentuent la pression sur les terroristes de lтАЩarm├йe Rwandaise ├а Rwindi LтАЩartillerie lourde des FARDC d├йtruit plusieurs positions des terroristes RDF, Le front de Rutshuru est tr├иs important, la lib├йration de Rutshuru isolera les terroristes du M23 de leurs base arri├иre qui est le Rwanda 

D├йploy├йe depuis le 15 d├йcembre de l'ann├йe derni├иre pour aider le gouvernement congolais ├а r├йtablir la paix et la s├йcurit├й dans l'est de la RDC face ├а la progression du M23, la force de la Mission de la SADC, jusqu'├а pr├йsent sans combat contre l'ennemi, rassure quant au respect des droits de l'homme et du droit international humanitaire en attendant son engagement aux combats.

le Pr├йsident Rwandais Paul Kagame recrute le Burkinab├и Lassina Zerbo dans son cabinet restreint. Selon un communiqu├й du Gouvernement Rwandais lтАЩancien premier ministre du Burkina Faso a int├йgr├й le cabinet restreint du pr├йsident rwandais Paul Kagame. Le docteur, Lassina Zerbo a directement adress├й ses remerciements au chef de l'├Йtat Rwandais. " Mes sinc├иres remerciements au President  @PaulKagame pour sa confiance : Fier dтАЩint├йgrer son cabinet . En plus des fonctions de Pr├йsident du Conseil d'administration", a d├йclar├й le nouveau homme de Kagame. LтАЩancien Premier ministre du Burkina int├иgre le cabinet en tant que Membre du Conseil strat├йgique et politique тАУ Conseiller en ├Йnergie. Et ce, en plus de ses fonctions de pr├йsident du Conseil dтАЩadministration de Rwanda Atomic Energy Board.

la guerre du M23 a de lourdes cons├йquences sur la population civile qui se retrouve sous les tirs de balles et dтАЩartillerie. En effet, M├йdecins sans fronti├иres qui intervient dans plusieurs camps des d├йplac├йs ├а Goma et ses environs rapporte avoir enregistr├й plus de 1500 bless├йs depuis le d├йbut de lтАЩann├йe. Ces chiffres concernent les provinces du Nord-Kivu et du Sud-Kivu o├╣ des projectiles dтАЩobus ont plusieurs fois touch├й des camps des d├йplac├йs. ┬л Depuis le d├йbut de lтАЩann├йe, on avait 110 cas de victimes sur 8 sites par jour. Et en avril sur trois sites avait plus de 700 cas. Pour le nombre des bless├йs au Sud-Kivu et au Nord-Kivu, parce quтАЩon avait une grosse d├йt├йrioration du c├┤t├й de Minova, on est ├а environ 1500 bless├йs qui ont ├йt├й re├зus depuis le d├йbut de lтАЩann├йe ┬╗, a d├йclar├й Marie Brun, coordinatrice dтАЩurgence pour M├йdecins Sans Fronti├иres ├а Goma. Dans ce contexte des affrontements permanents entre les Forces arm├йes de la R├йpublique d├йmocratique du Congo (FARDC) et les rebelles du M23, les activit├йs humanitaires sont constamment perturb├йes alors que les b├йn├йficiaires sont dans le besoin. 
 
Au moins 17 d├йtenus de la prison centrale de Shabunda se sont ├йvad├йs lundi 27 mai, Selon plusieurs sources, lтАЩ├йvasion a eu lieu dans la nuit. "Autour de 23H00, quelques coups de balles ont ├йt├й entendus. 17 prisonniers sur 44 ont r├йussi ├а tromper la vigilance des gardiens. Ils ont pris le large. Les policiers commis ├а la prison se sont mis ├а tirer alors que les ├йvad├йs ├йtaient d├йj├а loin du b├вtiment", dit Musky Kimengele, PCA du Cadre permanent de r├йflexion pour le d├йveloppement de Shabunda CPRDS. "Il y a 17 ├йvad├йs, tous condamn├йs par le tribunal de grande instance parmi eux les auteurs des viols", ajoute  Samy Kitambila, vice-pr├йsident de la soci├йt├й civile du Sud-Kivu. Le Cadre Permanent de r├йflexion pour le d├йveloppement de Shabunda ajoute ├йgalement qu'un policier a ├йt├й arr├кt├й mais quтАЩaucun ├йvad├й nтАЩa ├йt├й retrouv├й. тАЬCтАЩest inqui├йtant car ces malfrats circulent d├йsormais librement ├а travers nos villages, ce qui met notre population en ins├йcurit├й", note le CPRDS. Cette structure demande aux autorit├йs de diligenter une enqu├кte pour que les raisons de cette ├йvasion soient tir├йes au clair et que les coupables soient sectionn├йs.

title: Agression rwandaise : suivez l suite des actualit├йs politiques et s├йcuritaires de ce samedi 25/5/24
description:
Agression rwandaise : suivez la suite des actualit├йs politiques et s├йcuritaires de ce samedi 25/5/24 

Au total, quatre militaires des Forces arm├йes de la R├йpublique d├йmocratique du Congo (FARDC) sont aux arr├кts dans le groupement d'Irambi-Katana, en territoire de Kabare (Sud-Kivu). Ce, apr├иs des altercations entre les ├йl├йments de s├йcurit├й et la population locale ayant conduit ├а la mort de deux civils, le jeudi 23 mai 2024. Selon Joseph Cirimwengoma, administrateur du territoire de Kabare, ces quatre militaires seront jug├йs par la Cour militaire en audience foraine suite aux incidents du jeudi dernier. Il pr├йcise qu'apr├иs ces altercations, les autorit├йs ont d├йcid├й de permuter les militaires dans le centre de Katana. Dans un message rendu public le vendredi 24 mai, le gouverneur ├йlu du Sud-Kivu, Jean-Jacques Purusi, a d├йplor├й ces incidents, et a invit├й les services de s├йcurit├й ├а sanctionner les auteurs. Pour rappel, la nuit de mercredi et jeudi 23 mai dernier, un militaire a assassin├й un civil ├а son domicile et le matin, les habitants en col├иre ont ramen├й le cadavre au sous-commissariat de la Police de Katana. Pour disperser les manifestants, les services de s├йcurit├й ont tir├й des coups de feu, et un autre civil est d├йc├йd├й sur place.

Un enfant dтАЩenviron 13 ans est mort calcin├й lors de lтАЩincendie dтАЩune maison, dans la nuit de jeudi ├а vendredi ├а Beni, au Nord-Kivu. CтАЩest une maison en planche qui a pris feu au quartier Butsili, commune de Mulekera. A part la mort de cet enfant, la Soci├йt├й civile de Mulekera indique que des bless├йs et des d├йg├вts mat├йriels ont ├йt├й ├йgalement enregistr├йs. Son pr├йsident, Joseph Sabuni, lance un appel aux personnes de bonne volont├й, les invitant ├а venir ├а la rescousse de la famille ├йplor├йe qui est d├йsormais sans abris.

Plus de 600.000 d├йplac├йs fuyant la guerre au Nord-Kivu sont identifi├йs dans la cit├й de Minova en territoire de Kalehe, dans la province du Sud-Kivu. L'administrateur du territoire de Kalehe, Thomas Bakenga, qui le confirme, pr├йcise que ces d├йplac├йs de guerre vivent dans des conditions difficiles et plaident pour leur assistante. Thomas Bakenga regrette, cependant, de constater que son territoire est victime ├йgalement des bombes largu├йes ├а Kalehe par les rebelles du M23, qui causent au passage des morts et des bless├йs. L'administrateur du territoire de Kalehe souligne par ailleurs que la cit├й de Minova est actuellement enclav├йe suite au d├йlabrement des routes et l'ins├йcurit├й sur la voie lacustre. Il sied de signaler qu'au moins 10 personnes ont d├йj├а perdu la vie ├а Kalehe suite aux bombes largu├йes par les rebelles du M23/RDF.

Au moins 34 696 enfants vou├йs au d├йplacement suite aux affrontements entre les rebelles du M23/RDF et la coalition FARDC-Wazalendo dans le groupement Mutanda en territoire de Rutshuru au Nord-Kivu nтАЩont pas acc├иs aux cours depuis le d├йbut du mois de Mai de lтАЩann├йe scolaire en cours. Ces apprenants traversent des conditions d├йplorables faute dтАЩencadrement scolaires dans leurs milieux de refuge.  Le point focal de la veille humanitaire dans la chefferie de Bwito et au Sud du territoire de Lubero, ces ├йl├иves et ├йcoliers ├йparpill├йs dans les familles dтАЩaccueil, n├йcessitent dans lтАЩurgence une prise en charge et un encadrement de la part du gouvernement central et ses partenaires, ne fus ce que pour des apprentissages.  Paris Mastaki, parle dтАЩun manque ├а gagner et dтАЩun recul de la cr├иme intellectuelle de cette partie du territoire de Rutshuru. Il craint pour le futur de la prochaine soci├йt├й en g├йn├йral.  Au del├а de cette situation, la coordination de la veille humanitaire d├йplore les conditions inhumaines quтАЩendurent pr├иs de 14 000 nouveaux m├йnages qui se sont d├йplac├йs en d├йbut du mois de Mai fuyant des atrocit├йs dans le groupement Mutanda et prenant la direction des villages des groupements Kanyabayonga dans la chefferie de Bwito et Itala dans le territoire de Lubero. Elle rapporte ├йgalement un bilan dтАЩau moins 27 civils d├йc├йd├йs ├а lтАЩespace de 20 jours ce mois de Mai suivis des nombreux d├йg├вts mat├йriels dont des maisons d├йtruites par les obus jet├йs par les forces bellig├йrantes au cours des affrontements.
Manifestation ├а Berlin (Allemagne) contre Apple en raison de l'utilisation frauduleuse des minerais provenant de la RDC pour la fabrication des iPhones.

Doch nicht einmal die alarmierendsten Vorzeichnen lie├Яen ihn ahnen, zu welch grauenvoller Tat sein Sohn f├дhig war - ein Verbrechen, das die gesamte Nation schockieren sollte.

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: LIVE: Boyfriend Cop Murder Trial тАУ MA v. Karen Read тАУ Day 5

title: Mass. cold case turns into manhunt thanks to forensic technology
description:
This cold case languished in evidence rooms for decades, while two survivors wondered who had raped them in a retail store in 1989 and how he disappeared. With reporting from 5 Investigates, their case was given renewed attention and a closer inspection with forensic genetic genealogy. description:

Episode 279: A kidnapped Mother 
------------------------------------
A few hours ago, Men kidnaps a Mother and snatches from her daughter, as they deliberately beat her up and takes her mother away. she visits the nearest police station bleeding and helpless to file complaints against the kidnappers. What will happen next? will the police able to find her mother and the kidnappers?. Watch to know more.

About Crime Patrol : 
---------------------------------
Crime Patrol will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Law & Order: Criminal Intent - Abel and Willing
description:
Nichols (Jeff Goldblum) and Stevens (Saffron Burrows) are called to investigate after happily married couple Linda (Nadia Bowers) and Ted (Derek Cecil) are assaulted and sedated by a masked assailant while leaving the marina. Ted later emerges in a forest, confused and traumatized. Park workers discover him, and he says that he may have just killed his wife. Upon further examination, Linda's body reveals traces of an adhesive and suction cup marks. Captain

Callas (Mary Elizabeth Mastrantonio) recalls that there have been four similar killings around the country in recent years. As Detectives Nichols and Stevens pursue the case, they discover that motive can sometimes be harder to ascertain than the killer's identity.

title: Putin turned state into criminal organization: law does not work in Russia
description:
Criminalization of Russia. A full-scale war with Ukraine is leading to the dominance of criminals in Russia - in the armed forces, politics and economy. The Wagner Private Military Company, which is now dominated by inadequate and disenfranchised prisoners, is gaining more and more weight. Criminals are transferring prison practices to regular Russian units: hazing, beatings, rape, and even executions. At the same time, state propaganda not only presents mercenaries as heroes, but also encourages their criminal habits in every possible way. More details - in our story.

title: Cold Case: Wie vermoordde Hannie Bakker? | IN SAMENWERKING MET POLITIE
description:
In deze aflevering bezoeken we de plaats delict en spreken we de nabestaanden van het slachtoffer. Wij zijn gevraagd door de politie om mee te werken aan de Cold Case van Hannie Bakker. Een zaak die al 5 jaar op een oplossing wacht. Hannie Bakker werd met Koningsdag 2017 zwaargewond aangetroffen in haar woning en overleed een aantal weken later in het ziekenhuis. Wie sloop haar huis binnen en verrichtte deze verschrikkelijke daad?

Voor nabestaanden is het van groot belang dat de zaak wordt opgelost. De politie vraagt iedereen die iets weet over de zaak of over de mogelijke dader of daders zich te melden. 

Tipmogelijkheden:
De Opsporingstiplijn op nummer 0800-6070. 

Meld Misdaad Anoniem op nummer 0800-7000. Meldpunt Meld Misdaad Anoniem zorgt dat de tips niet herleidbaar zijn tot de tipgever en draagt de informatie dan pas over aan de politie. 

Wie vertrouwelijk contact wil met de politie kan bellen met het Team Criminele Inlichtingen via nummer: 072-5050015. 

Ook online is het mogelijk tips door te geven via het tipformulier op www.politie.nl/hanniebakker.  Informatie kan ook gemaild worden naar coldcase@politie.nl

Het is nooit te laat om te praten.

title: Crime Patrol - рдХреНрд░рд╛рдЗрдо рдкреЗрдЯреНрд░реЛрд▓ рд╕рддрд░реНрдХ - Ep 776 - Case 17/2017(Part 1) - 11th Mar, 2017
description:
Click here to Subscribe to SET Channel : https://www.youtube.com/user/setindia?sub_confirmation=1
Click to watch all the episodes of Crime Patrol - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupza0aEZ_FKj0mBguCdtwU_c
In today's episode of Crime Patrol, watch the investigation of a murder case from Punjab. The police find SurendraтАЩs dead body in a deserted place. They soon learn that Surendra is a property dealer from Ludhiana. While investigating SurendraтАЩs murder case, the police find out that Surendra had an extramarital affair. Will the police be able to solve the case? Stay tuned in to find the answer.
Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?'I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Crime Patrol - Bengali - Episode 77
description:
"Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, тАЬIt should not have happenedтАЭ.Would knowing the тАЬWhyтАЭ behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he looks at meтАЭ, тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he/she is behavingтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she is out of his/her mindтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she has gone crazyтАЭ. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Crime Patrol - The Way Out - Episode 406 - 15th August 2014
description:
Ep 406 - Crime Patrol Satark - This episode tracks down the story of 26-year old Rakhi Mathur of Ghaziabad, who paid the price of her unemployed husbandтАЩs undoing. Rakhi who was educated up till 12th standard, wanted to take up some job to support her husband but Jagat never allowed her to step out of the house. The torture on Rakhi went from mental to physical and she shared her trauma for the first time with her Parents and Brother. Jagat had other plans, he confronted Rakhi for subjecting him to public humiliation, alleged her of having an affair and even suspected that Ruchi was not his daughter. Who killed Rakhi? 

Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, тАЬIt should not have happenedтАЭ.Would knowing the тАЬWhyтАЭ behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he looks at meтАЭ, тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he/she is behavingтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she is out of his/her mindтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she has gone crazyтАЭ. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

Episode 844:
--------------------
Dead bodies of children are discovered on the river bank by villagers. The police arrive at the spot and are shocked to find that their throats have been slit. The police, in order to determine the identity of the victims, search the length and breath of Palkipur for any clues. The case takes a turn when the deadly body of a woman is discovered. The villagers are terrified of the murders. Is a serial killer involved in these murders? Or is it the work of a person who was known to the victims? Watch this episode to find out. 
 
Crime Patrol:
---------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?'I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Killer Cases: Sorority Girl Savagely Murdered After Getting in the Wrong Car
description:
In a devastating case that rocked the University of South Carolina community, "Killer Cases" investigates the brutal murder of 21-year-old college student Samantha Josephson. The bright and promising young life of this loving sister and dedicated member of the Alpha Delta Pi sorority was senselessly cut short in March 2019 after a night out with friends. In a tragic mix-up, Samantha mistakenly got into a vehicle she thought was her Uber ride, a mistake that would prove fatal.

Subscribe for more Law&Crime: https://bit.ly/LawAndCrimeNetwork

This episode provides an in-depth look at the Samantha Josephson murder case, detailing the horrific events that fateful night as well as the intensive investigation and manhunt that followed. Through interviews with law enforcement, legal experts, and those closest to Samantha, viewers are given a profound window into this devastating University of South Carolina college student murder.

title: Crime Patrol - рдХреНрд░рд╛рдЗрдо рдкреЗрдЯреНрд░реЛрд▓ рд╕рддрд░реНрдХ - Ep 820 - Case 41 / 2017 - 23rd Jun, 2017
description:
Click here to Subscribe to SetIndia Channel : https://www.youtube.com/user/setindia?sub_confirmation=1
Click to watch all the episodes of Crime Patrol Dial 100 - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupzBi22rTZgQbnRMWVCrUEvP

Episode 820:
--------------------
The police begin an investigation into the missing case of Sohail Baig. The police find that Sohail had arrived in India a few days earlier from Dubai. Naved, Sohail's close friend, is brought for questioning. But, the police fail to gather any information. The police suspect Sohail of having an affair and try to find the woman who was having an affair with him. What is the motive behind Sohail's murder? Watch this episode to find out. 

Crime Patrol:
----------------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?'I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

About Crime Patrol :
-----------------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Petra Nohl: Mord im Karneval nach 35 Jahren aufgekl├дrt? | Lokalzeit MordOrte
description:
Am Karnevals-Sonntag im Jahr 1988 ziehen die Umz├╝ge wie in jedem Jahr durch die K├╢lner Stadtteile. Doch nicht ├╝berall k├╢nnen die Jecken an diesem Tag ausgelassen feiern. Denn hinter einem Imbisswagen am Zugweg wird die Leiche einer jungen Frau gefunden. Es ist die damals 24-J├дhrige Petra Nohl. Noch in der Nacht hatte die junge Mutter in einer Disco Karneval gefeiert. #PetraNohl

Der Fall sorgt f├╝r Aufsehen, denn: F├╝r den Mittag ist am Fundort der Leiche ein Karnevalsumzug angesetzt. Die Polizei schafft es nicht mehr rechtzeitig, ihn umzuleiten. Es kommt zu bizarren Szenen: Karnevalisten ziehen an der Leiche vorbei, w├дhrend die Spurensicherung ihre Arbeit macht.

F├╝r die Polizei ist der Fall Petra Nohl 35 Jahre lange ein Cold Case. Bis zum 14. Februar 2023.
Auf den Tag genau 35 Jahre nach der Tat erreicht die MordOrte-Redaktion ein Anruf von der Polizei: ein mutma├Яlicher T├дter ist festgenommen. Es handelt sich dabei um einen 56-j├дhrigen Mann aus K├╢ln.

Nach der Ausstrahlung des Falles in der Sendung Aktenzeichen XY im Dezember, meldet sich ein Mann bei der Polizei und gibt den entscheidenden Hinweis auf den Tatverd├дchtigen. Er erinnert sich, dass er gemeinsam mit einem Bekannten in der Disco gefeiert hat, in der auch Petra Nohl war. Drau├Яen habe man die junge Frau dann noch getroffen. Der Bekannte sei ihr dann gefolgt. 
Eine DNA-Untersuchung bringt schlie├Яlich den Durchbruch.

Einer, der dar├╝ber sehr erleichtert ist, ist Markus Weber. Er leitet die Cold-Case-Einheit der Polizei in K├╢ln. Unsere Host Sarah hat f├╝r diesen Film noch vor der Festnahme mit ihm gesprochen. Im Interview erz├дhlt er auch, warum es ├╝ber Jahre so schwer war, einen T├дter zu finden. 

Noch ein Hinweis zum Film: Bei 13:35 seht und h├╢rt ihr den K├╢lner Staatsanwalt Bastian Blaut. Hier ist uns ein Fehler unterlaufen und wir haben den falschen Namen eingeblendet.  Wir bitten, den Fehler zu entschuldigen.

Wichtig: Der Fall Petra Nohl zeigt, dass es auch Jahre sp├дter noch m├╢glich ist, einen Cold Case aufzukl├дren. Dabei kann nur ein Hinweis entscheidend sein. Wir haben hier bereits ├╝ber mehrere Cold-Case-F├дlle berichtet. Hinweise nimmt jede Polizeidienststelle entgegen.

title: LIVE: Karen Swift Murder Trial тАФ TN v. David Swift тАФ Day Two
description:
David Swift is accused of murdering his wife, Karen Swift, in October 2011, after she was found dead in an old Tennessee cemetery. David was allegedly the last person to see her alive after she returned home from a Halloween party. When David was arrested, he had remarried and was living with another woman in Alabama. David has been charged with premeditated first-degree murder and could face life behind bars.

That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Cold case S03E05 Only You
Crime Patrol - рдХреНрд░рд╛рдЗрдо рдкреЗрдЯреНрд░реЛрд▓ рд╕рддрд░реНрдХ - Ep 795 - Case 28 / 2017 (Part 3) - 23rd Apr, 2017
description:
Click here to Subscribe to SetIndia Channel : https://www.youtube.com/user/setindia?sub_confirmation=1
Click to watch all the episodes of Crime Patrol Satark - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupza0aEZ_FKj0mBguCdtwU_c
The episode continues with the investigation of GitaтАЩs missing children. Rajiv tells the police that he had murdered Gita as she was blackmailing him to marry her. He also admits that he had abandoned Krishna and Sakshi in a train. Will the police be able to solve the case? Stay tuned in to find the answer.
Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?'I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

About the show:
--------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

En 1994, les d├йput├йs d├йcident d'instaurer des peines de prison "incompressibles├й. Elles peuvent aller jusqu'├а trente ans et ne sont pas r├йvisables. Une affaire a beaucoup compt├й dans cette d├йcision : l'affaire Van Geloven. Van Geloven est multir├йcidiviste d├йj├а condamn├й a deux reprises, en 1984 et 1991. Isabelle Knegt, sa soeur adoptive, t├йmoigne pour la premi├иre fois : Van Geloven l'a agress├йe sexuellement entre l'├вge de 5 et 12 ans. Elle a essay├й d'informer la justice des agissements pass├йs de Van geloven. N├йgligence ? Au proc├иs de 1984 la justice ne prend m├кme pas la peine d'├йvoquer la d├йposition d'Isabelle. title: The Murder Case Shocked Public US 2019 | Jassy Correia & Louis Coleman - Her Body is in the Suitcase
description:
In 2019, Jassy Correia, a 23-year-old woman, became a tragic victim of kidnapping and murder. The case began with her disappearance after celebrating her 23rd birthday at a nightclub in Boston. Louis Coleman was accused of kidnapping Correia outside the nightclub in the early hours of February 24, 2019, and subsequently killing her.

Prosecutors detailed that after abducting Correia, Coleman carried her body into his apartment in Providence. In the days following, he bought cleaning materials and conducted internet searches on disposing of a body. Correia's body was eventually found in a suitcase in the trunk of ColemanтАЩs car during a traffic stop in Delaware. The discovery was particularly harrowing as her body was found duct-taped and in a fetal position, with evidence suggesting she had been strangled and sexually assaulted.

In today's episode of Crime Patrol, watch the investigation of a murder case from Mumbai. Smruti and Ankit find their mother Anjali lying in the pool of blood in their house. The police reach the venue to investigate AnjaliтАЩs murder. The police find out that Anjali had prevented her sister Arpita from marrying her boyfriend in the past. Will the police be able to solve the case? Stay tuned in to find the answer.
Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?'I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Harlem Drug Wars - Man Caught 25 Years Later For Cold Case Double Murder - Franklin Plaza
description:
A Bronx man was been nabbed in a decades-old cold case involving the murders of two teens found shot in the head on a school rooftop in East Harlem. Ramon Solla, 45, was arrested in mid October of 2019, and charged with the 1995 slayings of Ricky Santiago and Christopher Toro-Rossy, a double homicide resulting from a heroin deal gone bad, prosecutors said. The boys, both 17, were found with gunshot wounds to their heads on the rooftop of Park East High School at 230 East 105th Street in the early hours of March 3, 1995. Both were pronounced dead at the scene. Solla, known as тАЬRayтАЭ or тАЬR.B,тАЭ was 21 when he allegedly gunned down the teens as part of a conspiracy to distribute more than a kilogram of heroin, prosecutors said. From approximately 1994 through 1995, two crews shared drug territory on the block  of 106th Street between 1st Avenue and 2nd Avenue in Manhattan (the тАЬBlockтАЭ). One crew occupied territory closer to 1 st Avenue and was led by Mark Rodriguez. The second crew occupied territory closer to 2nd Avenue and was led by Carmelo Sanchez. By agreement, both crews v/ere permitted to sell heroin on their respective sides of the Block.
Solla was a member of Rodriguez's crew, along with Carlos Alvarez, Amado Vega, and Nathaniel Parker. The murder victims, Ricky Santiago and Christopher Torro, were among the kids in Rodriguez's crew who actually conducted the hand-to-hand sales. The crew sold heroin by operating in shifts every day from 1994 through March 1995, distributing quantities far exceeding one kilogram of heroin.
Around early 1995, tensions began to rise between Rodriguez and Alvarez, caused, at least in part, by trouble they were having with Sanchez. For example, Rodriguez believed that Alvarez had burglarized his home and stolen drug proceeds. As a result, when Rodriguez learned that Sanchez was planning to kill both Rodriguez and Alvarez, Rodriguez fled the Block but did not warn Alvarez. Ultimately, members of Rodriguez's crew took sides: Torro and Santiago sided with Rodriguez, while Solla, Vega, and Parker sided with Alvarez.

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: TESTAMENT DE JOSEPH DESIR├Й MOBUTU SUR L'AGRESSION RWANDAISE ET LA COMPLICIT├Й DES OCCIDENTAUX
description:
LE TESTAMENT DU MAR├ЙCHAL MOBUTU
"Un monde dans un monde qui monde le monde"
APR├ИS MOI LE D├ЙLUGE...

EXCLUSIF : le testament de Mobutu sur lтАЩagression
Enfin, le testament politique du Mar├йchal Mobutu est d├йvoil├й. LтАЩancien pr├йsident de la R├йpublique du Za├пre est mort en laissant un h├йritage de profondes r├йv├йlations sur la d├йstabilisation de la RDC pendant des d├йcennies. Avant de mourir, Mobutu Sese Seko Kuku Ngbendu Wa Zabanga sтАЩ├йtait confi├й ├а lтАЩun de ses proches qui a d├йcid├й, 25 ans apr├иs, dтАЩ├йclairer le peuple congolais afin quтАЩil prenne la mesure du danger pour sa survie.

Par Landry Amisi

LтАЩex-pr├йsident du Congo-Za├пre, le mar├йchal Mobutu dont le testament racont├й par son confident Jean-Pierre Mumba Etumba, met ├а nu 25 ans apr├иs, le complot de balkanisation du Congo-Kinshasa @Photo Droits tiers

publi├й le 29 novembre 2022 ├а 07:29:00
Jean-Pierre Mumba Etumba, un des premiers opposants au r├йgime de Mobutu en Belgique apr├иs avoir dirig├й la JMPR/Belgique (Jeunesse du Mouvement populaire pour la r├йvolution), sort de son silence et livre ├а la nation congolaise le secret de lтАЩextermination des populations congolaises par les dirigeants occidentaux.

Lire aussi :
Des Rwandais du M23 seraient infiltr├йs dans le contingent k├йnyan
R├йconcili├й avec le Mar├йchal le 12 mars 1980 ├а Bruxelles, Jean-Pierre Mumba Etumba rentra au pays et fut lтАЩun des tr├иs proches conseillers du d├йfunt pr├йsident. Rest├й aux c├┤t├йs de Mobutu jusquтАЩ├а sa mort, il d├йcide de sensibiliser le peuple congolais tout entier sur le danger qui guette la R├йpublique d├йmocratique du Congo.

Jeudi 15 mai 1997, au camp Tshatshi ├а 17 heures, le Mar├йchal Mobutu mтАЩinvita ├а d├оner avec deux autres personnalit├йs, Sokoni Louis, ancien secr├йtaire particulier et confident de Patrice Emery Lumumba et le professeur Djembi Mwembo, ancien directeur ├а la Francophonie ├а Paris. Il nous re├зut ├а trois. Apr├иs avoir discut├й, il mтАЩa tir├й de c├┤t├й pour me confier un secret, ouvre-t-il la poudri├иre. Mobutu se savait mourant. Il se conjuguait lui-m├кme d├йj├а au pass├й tout en gardant un souci pointu pour lтАЩavenir de son peuple.
Clinton, Mitterrand, Thatcher, roi Baudouin au c┼Уur du complot de balkanisation de la RDC
LтАЩex-pr├йsident Mobutu, au soir de sa vie terrestre, nтАЩa pas voulu laisser son peuple dans lтАЩignorance. Expos├й ├а lтАЩextermination, le peuple congolais devrait savoir dтАЩo├╣ vient le complot qui comptabilise aujourdтАЩhui 10 millions de morts en R├йpublique d├йmocratique du Congo.

Mobutu confia ├а Jean-Pierre Mumba Etumba ceci : тАЬNotre pays, le Za├пre sera divis├й. Les occidentaux ont d├йcid├й de saucissonner notre pays car, pour eux, nous ne m├йritons pas ce paysтАЭ, a-t-il expliqu├й. Jean-Pierre Mumba Etumba r├йv├иle m├кme les chefs dтАЩ├Йtat des pays qui ont d├йcid├й de lтАЩ├йlimination des Congolais, par tous les moyens pour parvenir ├а leur objectif. тАЬCeux qui ont mont├й ce complot sont les pr├йsidents Bill Clinton des ├Йtats-Unis dтАЩAm├йrique, Fran├зois Mitterrand de la France, Helmut Kohl dтАЩAllemagne, Margaret Thatcher de la Grande-Bretagne, le Roi Baudouin et son Premier ministre de BelgiqueтАЭ, ├йnum├иre-t-il. Ils ont mis en place un laboratoire o├╣ nтАЩont ├йt├й recrut├йs que des savants blancs, poursuivra Mobutu. Leur mission ├йtait dтАЩ├йtudier comment r├йaliser leur projet de balkaniser le Za├пre (RDC). тАЬJe nтАЩai aucune id├йe du lieu o├╣ ce laboratoire se trouverait. Mais il est install├й quelque part, dans lтАЩun des pays impliqu├йsтАЭ, avait ├йclair├й le L├йopard peu avant sa mort. Jean-Pierre Mumba Etumba r├йv├иle, en outre, que les cinq grandes puissances se sont r├йparties le g├вteau Za├пre (RDC). тАЬLes Am├йricains voudraient prendre lтАЩEst, cтАЩest-├а-dire, les trois Kivu (Nord-Kivu, Sud-Kivu, Maniema) et la Province orientale ; les Britanniques veulent sтАЩemparer des deux Kasa├п, oriental et occidental (actuellement subdivis├йs en quatre provinces); les Allemands ont choisi le Bandundu et le Bas-Zaire (Kongo central); les Fran├зais se sont appropri├йs le Shaba (grand Katanga); les Belges ont pris lтАЩEquateur, le Ma├п-Ndombe et KinshasaтАЭ, a-t-il d├йtaill├й. Mumba justifie le choix belge du Ma├п-Ndombe. Une entit├й r├йserv├йe jadis au roi L├йopold II. тАЬPourquoi le Ma├п-Ndombe ? CтАЩest parce que lorsque le roi L├йopold II avait c├йd├й lтАЩ├Йtat ind├йpendant du Congo ├а la Belgique, il avait gard├й la partie Ma├п-Ndombe pour lui-m├кmeтАЭ, a-t-il expliqu├й.

├Йliminer toute lтАЩ├йlite congolaise, raser nos villages et installer un peuple dominant
Dans ce complot, raconte le confident du Mar├йchal Mobutu, les occidentaux maniganceraient dтАЩexterminer progressivement le peuple congolais et de le remplacer par une peuplade nilotique. тАЬIls vont ex├йcuter tous les acteurs politiques, tous les hommes dтАЩaffaires, tous les chefs coutumiers et raser tous les villages. Mes g├йn├йraux qui mтАЩont trahi, seront tous tu├йs ou assassin├йs.

About Crime Patrol :
-----------------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Coldcase: Willeke Dost - 15 januari 1992 (aankondiging)
description:
Coldcase: Willeke Dost
Vermist
15 januari 1992
Koekange тАУ Drenthe

Oproep: Annemarie Eleveld - Vriendin van Willeke

Wat is er gebeurd?

Willeke Dost (15) is sinds 15 januari 1992, al ruim dertig jaar, vermist. Op de ochtend van 15
januari was Willeke niet thuis en haar fiets stond niet meer in de schuur. De pleegouders van
Willeke raakten niet direct in paniek, omdat ze dachten dat Willeke al vroeg naar school was
gegaan. Die middag kwam Willeke echter niet thuis van school en bleek dat zij nooit op
school is geweest. Haar pleegouders hebben haar toen als vermist opgegeven. In eerste
instantie is de vermissing door de politie beschouwd als een vrijwillige verdwijning en
vanwege weinig tips is het onderzoek al snel afgeschaald.

Wie was Willeke?

Willeke heeft een zware jeugd gehad. Toen Willeke net ├й├йn jaar oud was, zijn haar ouders om
het leven gekomen tijdens een verkeersongeluk. Ze is opgegroeid bij familie, in verschillende
opvangtehuizen en in pleeggezinnen. Willeke was een kwetsbaar en beschadigd meisje. Op
tienjarige leeftijd kwam Willeke terecht bij het pleeggezin in Koekange. Daar leek zij wat op
te bloeien, maar er waren ook problemen in het gezin.

Hoe staat het er nu voor?

Opsporing Verzocht en Peter R. de Vries besteden begin 2000 regelmatig aandacht aan deze
verdwijning, maar de tips die daaruit voortkwamen leveren niets op. In 2010 leek er een
doorbraak te zijn. De pleegmoeder en pleegbroer van Willeke werden gearresteerd en er werd
een zoekactie gedaan naar Willeke in het weiland achter de boerderij van haar pleegouders.
De zoekactie leverde echter niets op en de pleegmoeder en pleegbroer werden weer
vrijgelaten. Amateurspeurders lieten het er echter niet bij zitten, zij startten zelf zoekacties. Zo
werden er na de inzet van speurhonden en een grondradar verdachte sporen gevonden in het
weiland achter de boerderij van de pleegouders van Willeke. Vanwege de vele media-
aandacht heeft de politie in 2018 uiteindelijk besloten om toch nog een zoekactie te houden in
dit weiland, helaas ook zonder resultaat.

Familie

Willeke haar familie, vriendinnen en de vele mensen die om haar geven willen niks liever dan
weten wat er met haar is gebeurd. Ervan uitgaande dat zij niet meer in leven is, zou ze een
mooi afscheid verdienen en een plekje in het graf bij haar ouders. Haar jeugdvriendin
Annemarie Eleveld doet daarom een oproep: тАЬEr moeten mensen zijn die meer weten en die
dus al 32 jaar hun mond houden.тАЭ

http://fr.euronews.com/2013/12/26/les-occidentaux-condamnent-l-agression-d-une-journaliste-en-ukraine
Tetiana Chornovil a ├йt├й attaqu├йe pr├иs de Kiev, la capitale. Tout a commenc├й par un accident de voiture provoqu├йe par un v├йhicule qui se trouvait devant le sien. Notre consoeur, journaliste proche de l'opposition a ├йt├й pass├йe ├а tabac par des hommes dont deux ont ├йt├й arr├кt├йs et un troisi├иme identifi├й. La police ├йvoque une vengeance, une ├йventuelle provocation isol├йe ou un simple accident de la route. Tetiana Chornovil souffre d'une fracture du nez et de contusions. L'opposition a appel├й ├а une manifestation de soutien d├иs dimanche. 

Tetiana Chornovil est connue pour ses enqu├кtes sur la corruption dans la haute administration et la classe dirigeante. Elle venait de publier un article consacr├й au riche patrimoine de plusieurs hauts dirigeants du pouvoir notamment le ministre de l'Int├йrieur et sa suppos├йe maison ou encore le golf et la maison flottante du pr├йsident Ianoukovitch. 

Ces derniers jours, Tetiana Chornovil avait pris publiquement la parole lors de plusieurs manifestations pro-europ├йennes et anti-pouvoir sur la place Maidan. Un mouvement entam├й il y a plusieurs semaines apr├иs la volte-face du pr├йsident Ianoukovtch qui a refus├й de signer un partenariat avec l'Union europ├йenne au profit d'une entente financi├иre et gazi├иre avec le voisin russe.

------------------------------------------------
When Nirmala Thakur is found dead in her house, the suspicion turns towards her husband Nishikant and neighbor Smita, as they were having a clandestine affair. Though the police initially believe it to be a case of contract killing, after a while, they find various other suspects with an intent to kill Nirmala. Who really killed Nirmala? LetтАЩs find out.

About Crime Patrol : 
---------------------------------
Crime Patrol will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.
