title: Ankur Arora Murder Case
description: Rohan (Arjun Mathur) was a young medical intern who dared to dream. He was in awe of Dr. Asthana (Kay Kay Menon), the Chief of Surgery of the Shekhawat General Hospital. All he wanted to was be like him. He lived in with Riya, his co-intern and the love of his life. However, when an eight year old boy, Ankur dies due to Dr. Asthana's medical negligence, Rohan realises that a good surgeon is not necessarily a good person. Together with Ankur's mother Nandita, Rohan sets out on a turbulent journey to fight for what is right. A fight for justice against his mentor, the hospital and the love of his life.

title: 2 men charged for elderly woman's murder in Tukwila Costco parking lot
description:
TUKWILA, Wash. тАФ Prosecutors have charged two men for the murder of a 67-year-old woman who was killed during an attempted robbery in the parking lot of the Costco in Tukwila in January.

According to court filings, Ilyiss Mohamud Abdi, 18, of Burien, and Salman Haji, 19, of Des Moines, face charges of murder in the first degree, robbery in the first degree, and attempted robbery in the first degree.

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

description:

In today's episode of Crime Patrol, watch the investigation of a murder case from Uttarakhand. When Rabiya goes missing from her house, her family lodge the complaint in a police station. The police find a dead body in a jungle. They soon find out that the body belongs to Rabiya. Want to know more? Then stay tuned in and find out here.
Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, тАЬIt should not have happenedтАЭ.Would knowing the тАЬWhyтАЭ behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he looks at meтАЭ, тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he/she is behavingтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she is out of his/her mindтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she has gone crazyтАЭ. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: JonBenet Ramsey | Does DNA Clear Ramsey Family | A Real Cold Case Detective's Opinion
description:
Did DNA really clear the Ramsey family in the murder of JonBenet? Why is John Ramsey pushing for more DNA testing, Does that mean he has nothing to hide? 

Lets see what nationally renowned cold case detective Ken Mains thinks as he dives in the deep waters to get to the truth.

About Ken Mains: You have seen him on the History Channel tracking the Zodiac Killer and on the Discovery Science Channel investigating history's greatest mysteries. Most recently he can be seen on the Reelz Channel giving his expert opinion on the "When Friends Speak" true crime series. 

Detective Mains served a combined 20 years in law enforcement and the United States Marine Corps. You read his best-selling autobiography 'Unsolved No More.' It is said he is "one of this countries greatest detectives" and the foremost authority on unsolved cold cases. He is raw, unfiltered and only cares about the truth. 

The credentials are there: USMC Veteran, Bachelors Degree (Criminal Justice), Masters Degree Studies (Criminal Profiling), Patrol Officer, Undercover Narcotics, FBI Task Force, District Attorney's Office, Drug Task Force Supervisor and Cold Case Detective. He is the founder of AISOCC, where he led the worlds best investigators including the Homicide Hunter Joe Kenda, Dr. Werner Spitz, Dr. Henry Lee, Dr. Mary Ellen O'Toole and Dr. Cyril Wecht, Jim Clemente, Bob Keppel to name a few. description:

It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Agression RDF/M23/AFC : Mirangi en feu des FARDC/Wazawaza, RDF en d├йbandade ce mercredi 29/5/24
description:
Agression RDF/M23/AFC : Mirangi en feu des FARDC, RDF en d├йbandade ce mercredi 29/5/24

Les combats se poursuivent entre FARDC et M23 dans le territoire de Rutshuru en province du Nord-Kivu, depuis maintenant 4 jours. Depuis le matin de ce mercredi 29 Mai, dтАЩintenses combats sont signal├йs au tour de Mirangi, une localit├й situ├йe dans le groupement Mutanda. Selon des sources locales, les rebelles du M23 appuy├йs par lтАЩarm├йe rwandaise veulent ├йchapper en passant par Lusoha pour atteindre Kanyabayonga mais les jeunes patriotes Wazalendo et les Forces arm├йes de la RDC continue ├а an├йantir la progression des rebelles. Pendant ce temps, dans le territoire de Masisi, des combats ont repris dans les collines de Nduma, Lukala et Makabya. L├а-bas, les Wazalendo continue toujours ├а repousser lтАЩennemi qui ne sait pas progresser. Des rebelles qui sont accus├йs dтАЩavoir neutralise des civils dans le Kikuku. Il sтАЩagit de trois hommes pris en otage et oblig├йs dтАЩacheminer les munitions sur la premi├иre ligne de front ├а Malianga. De retour, indique une source locale, ces hommes visiblement ├йpuis├йs se sont repos├йs ├а Bulibuli o├╣ une bombe lanc├йe par le M23 ├а partir de Rusizi sous contr├┤le de lтАЩennemi, leur est tomb├йe dessus, 9 personnes ont perdu la vie et 6 autres gri├иvement bless├йes dont des femmes qui fuyaient les affrontements.

Apr├иs 24 heures de kidnapping, deux personnes ont ├йt├й retrouv├йes sans vie, le mardi 28 mai 2024, dans le village de Kimbau situ├й dans le groupement Bambumba-Kisiki, territoire de Beni, au Nord-Kivu. ├А en croire Bravo Vukulu, ancien pr├йsident de la soci├йt├й civile du groupement Bambumba-Kisiki, ces civils ont ├йt├й pris en otage par les rebelles ADF lors de leur incursion signal├йe, lundi 27 mai, dans la localit├й de Kokola. Il fait savoir que les corps sans vie de ces civils abandonn├йs ont ├йt├й retrouv├йs par les agriculteurs. Les victimes sont un homme et une femme. Ces civils ont ├йt├й ex├йcut├йs par les rebelles des Forces d├йmocratiques et alli├йes, auteurs de leur enl├иvement. Cette situation a cr├й├й une psychose au sein des habitants de Kokola ┬╗, explique-t-il. Cet ancien pr├йsident de la soci├йt├й civile sтАЩinsurge contre cette ├йni├иme forme dтАЩins├йcurit├й. Il pense quтАЩil est temps que les autorit├йs militaires lancent les op├йrations militaires dans les environs du groupement Bambumba-Kkisiki o├╣ des mouvements suspects sont, ce dernier temps, signal├йs.


Un ├йl├йment de lтАЩarm├йe Ougandaise a recu son billet aller simple au cours dтАЩune attaque qui a cibl├й les Forces Arm├йes de la R├йpublique D├йmocratique du Congo (FARDC) lundi 27 mai 2024 ├а Mundubiena, une agglom├йration situ├йe dans le territoire de Beni au Nord-Kivu. Nos sources soup├зonnent les terroristes islamistes dтАЩAllied Democratic Forces (ADF) dтАЩ├кtre ├а la base de cette attaque. Elles parlent dтАЩun ├йl├йment FARDC bless├й par balle et deux jeeps incendi├йes par les assaillants. DтАЩapr├иs Rocky Muvunga, bourgmestre de la commune rurale de Mangina, les victimes ont ├йt├й cibl├йes par lтАЩennemi alors quтАЩelle faisaient la garde de ces v├йhicules au moment o├╣ la d├йl├йgation conduite par le commandant r├йgiment de la place ├йtait ├а Kudu-Kudu pour sтАЩencqu├йrir de la situation apr├иs des alertes de la population sur le mouvement des ADF. Arriv├йs ├а Mundubiena, ils ├йtaient oblig├йs de laisser les jeeps et motos ├а cet endroit suite ├а lтАЩimpraticabilit├й de la route. Et sont travers├йs ├а pieds jusquтАЩ├а Kudukudu. Alors de retour, ils ont entendu des coups de balles de loin. Visiblement, lтАЩennemi qui suivait leur mouvement a attaqu├й ceux qui gardaient les jeeps. Le mouvement des ADF est signal├й dans plusieurs agglom├йrations du territoire de Beni. La soci├йt├й civile d├йnonce le rel├вchement des op├йrations militaires, qui selon elle, est ├а la base de cette situation.

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Apr├иs l'agression du 22 nov.1970 : verdict du tribunal r├йvolutionnaire supr├кme au stade
description:
Apr├иs l'├йchec de l'agression portugaise du 22 Novembre 1970 qui a connu la participation effective de plusieurs pays , dont la France et l'Allemagne F├йd├йrale , et de l'OTAN, toutes soutenant le Portugal. 

Le peuple de Guin├йe et son ├Йtat r├йvolutionnaire ont r├йpondu effectivement ├а cette action nocive ├а laquelle ont particip├й des anciens guin├йens de l'arm├йe coloniale fran├зaise, guin├йens ├а double nationalit├йs, opposants, exil├йs , et autres mercenaires recrut├йs. Les soutiens forts du Portugal ont permis d'assurer le recrutement, la formation, l'├йquipement et le d├йbarquement. En plus de toute cette coalition ext├йrieure, des complicit├йs internes (en Guin├йe) doivent faciliter le d├йbarquement et le succ├иs de cette agression.

L'op├йration eu lieu effectivement dans l'avantage de la nuit (2h du matin), mais conna├оtra un ├йchec cuisant, malgr├й les centaines de citoyens et militaires guin├йens tu├йs dans la d├йfense de la Patrie par la brutalit├й de cette attaque.

_ Le tribunal r├йvolutionnaire Supr├кme groupant les structures judiciaires et les organes politiques du pays se chargera de juger les mercenaires arr├кt├йs, et les complices int├йrieurs et ext├йrieurs non-arr├кt├йs. Le nombre d'instance impliqu├й dans proc├иs fera de lui , l'un des plus grands proc├иs de l'histoire.
Le Tribunal R├йvolutionnaire Supr├кme donne son verdict au stade du 28 Septembre de Conakry. Les peines vont de prison ferme ├а dur├йe d├йtermin├йe , de travaux forc├йs , des saisis de biens et des condamn├йs ├а mort suivant les cat├йgories de personnes (├йtablies en fonction du тАЬdegr├й" de participation). La lib├йralisation de plusieurs dizaines de personnes avaient ├йgalement ├йt├й prononc├йe.

title: Ronald Castree - Cold Case Killers
description:
Lesley Molseed's twisted killer was finally caught. The 11-year-old's murder sparked a huge manhunt after she was stabbed 12 times and sexually assaulted after disappearing from her home in Rochdale.
A vulnerable man with learning difficulties, was eventually found to be innocent after 16 years behind bars - which has since been named one of the worst miscarriages of justice in UK history. Some 12 years later the real killer was found out by advances in DNA technology.

title: Doorbraak in cold case dankzij forensische wetenschap
description:
In september 1999 werd een jonge vrouw gevonden in een kliko in de rivier de Gaasp bij Amsterdam. Al 24 jaar wacht ze op een naam. Forensisch rechercheur Carina van Leeuwen is onvermoeibaar in haar zoektocht naar de identiteit van het klikomeisje. Ze grijpt alle nieuwe ontwikkelingen in de forensische wetenschap aan om meer informatie over haar te verzamelen. De forensische technieken zijn sinds de moord zodanig verbeterd dat ze hoopt dat het nu wel mogelijk is om haar een naam te geven.

Op ntr.nl/wetenschap vind je de mooiste wetenschapsverhalen van de NTR. We volgen met een kritische blik de ontwikkelingen in de wetenschap en houden je op de hoogte van het laatste wetenschapsnieuws, nieuwe programma's en leuke weetjes.

title: Trump's defense delivers closing arguments in hush money criminal trial
description:
Donald Trump's defense delivered over two hours of closing arguments Tuesday in the former president's hush money criminal trial. Trump's attorney attacked the credibility of the prosecution's star witness, Michael Cohen, painting him as a liar.

Prosecutors are expected to give their lengthy closing arguments before the jury begins deliberations later in the day.

title: Agression rwandaise : suivez la suite des actualit├йs s├йcuritaires et politiques de ce 27/5/24
description:
Agression rwandaise : suivez la suite des actualit├йs s├йcuritaires et politiques de ce 27/5/24

Depuis plus dтАЩune semaine, les affrontements ont repris de plus belle entre les FARDC et les rebelles du M23, soutenus par le Rwanda. L'arm├йe congolaise b├йn├йficie de l'appui des Wazalendo. Cette recrudescence des hostilit├йs fait suite ├а une offensive lanc├йe par les FARDC sur plusieurs fronts, avec pour objectif de reprendre le contr├┤le de certaines localit├йs dans les territoires de Masisi et de Rutshuru. Longtemps accus├йe de laxisme, lтАЩarm├йe congolaise est plus d├йtermin├йe que jamais. Cette d├йtermination renouvel├йe est en partie due ├а l'absence de progr├иs notables sur le front diplomatique, les initiatives de m├йdiation, en particulier le processus de Nairobi, ├йtant au point mort. Ce processus a rencontr├й des difficult├йs dтАЩimpl├йmentation, exacerb├йes par une crise de confiance majeure entre le pr├йsident congolais F├йlix Tshisekedi et son homologue kenyan, William Ruto. De plus, les autorit├йs congolaises affirment quтАЩelles nтАЩont jamais totalement abandonn├й lтАЩoption militaire, surtout en raison du manque dтАЩefforts de Kigali pour retirer ses troupes, toujours pr├йsentes sur le sol congolais. Cette pr├йsence continue alimente la d├йtermination des FARDC ├а poursuivre lтАЩoffensive pour prot├йger la souverainet├й nationale, explique un membre du cabinet de F├йlix Tshisekedi. Cette posture est nourrie par la dynamique sur le terrain militaire o├╣ les FARDC ont r├йcemment renforc├й leurs capacit├йs avec lтАЩarriv├йe de nouvelles troupes sur la ligne de front et lтАЩaugmentation des moyens a├йriens militaires. Ce renforcement vise ├а intensifier la pression sur le M23 et ├а pr├йparer le terrain pour lтАЩentr├йe en sc├иne prochaine des troupes de la Communaut├й de d├йveloppement de lтАЩAfrique australe (SADC). Les sources au sein de cette force assurent que lтАЩacheminement du mat├йriel militaire va sтАЩacc├йl├йrer dans les semaines ├а venir, offrant ainsi un soutien logistique et strat├йgique aux op├йrations en cours. En outre, un nouveau bataillon des FARDC est pr├кt ├а Lubumbashi et est sur le point d'├кtre d├йploy├й au Nord-Kivu pour faire face ├а la r├йbellion du M23. Il sтАЩagit du deuxi├иme bataillon de la brigade тАЬLes AiglonsтАЭ qui va appuyer SAMIRDC d├йj├а pr├йsente dans la zone. Avec ce d├йploiement suppl├йmentaire, les FARDC esp├иrent renforcer leurs positions sur le terrain. La province du Nord-Kivu compte ├а ce jour plus de 3 millions de d├йplac├йs suite ├а la guerre dтАЩagression quтАЩimpose ├а la RDC son voisin, le Rwanda, sous couvert du M23. Selon les humanitaires, la crise humanitaire due ├а cette guerre n├йcessite plus de 2 milliards USD et la mobilisation ├а ce jour est de moins de 20 % des fonds.

l'arm├йe congolaise repousse une nouvelle tentative de la coalition M23_RDF_AFC ├а Kyaghala en territoire de Rutshuru , elle a neutralis├й et captur├й d'autres. " Des d├йtonations d'armes lourdes et l├йg├иres ont ├йt├й entendues ce dimanche 26 mai ├а Kyaghala ├а +_ 30 Km de Kanyabayonga. L'arm├йe congolaise appuy├йe par des jeunes r├йsistants Wazalendo ont repouss├й l'enemi qui voulait d├йborder ├а Kyaghala. 12 parmi les M23_RDF ont ├йt├й captur├йs et plusieurs autres neutralis├йs", confie une source militaire dans la zone. D'apr├иs cette source, les ├йl├йments de la coalition M23_RDF_AFC n'ont pas pu faire face aux FARDC, ils ont port├й la tenue de l'arm├йe congolaise pour se faire passer pour les  @FARDC_off mais cette tactique a vite ├йt├й d├йcouverte. "Un engagement corps ├а corps FARDC M23 n'a jamais eu lieu. Tant├┤t ils donnent de l'argent aux brebis galeuse pour leur vendre les positions de l'arm├йe et d├йcrocher un repli ou soit d├йborder et prendre la population pour bouclier humain", pr├йcise la source.

description:
In today's episode of Crime Patrol, watch the investigation of a murder case from Haryana. Lalit's family find him dead on his bed. Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, тАЬIt should not have happenedтАЭ.Would knowing the тАЬWhyтАЭ behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he looks at meтАЭ, тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he/she is behavingтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she is out of his/her mindтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she has gone crazyтАЭ. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

description:
"Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, тАЬIt should not have happenedтАЭ.Would knowing the тАЬWhyтАЭ behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he looks at meтАЭ, тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he/she is behavingтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she is out of his/her mindтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she has gone crazyтАЭ. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. title: Dossier Van Den Heuvel - Pieter Hoovers - Cold case
description:
Reportageserie waarin misdaadverslaggever John van den Heuvel de hele wereld over reist om slachtoffers van criminaliteit bij te staan. Samen met zijn team pakt hij verschillende vormen van misdaad aan en geeft hij een ongepolijste inkijk in zijn missie naar gerechtigheid.

De 54-jarige Pieter en 32-jarige Tae Hoovers worden in de zomer van 2017 doodgeschoten in een woning in Amsterdam. De slachtoffers wonen in Thailand, maar verblijven op dat moment even in Nederland. De politie heeft de zaak nog altijd niet opgelost en daarom vraagt Pieters zus John om hulp. Ze reizen samen naar Thailand en daar achterhaalt John belangrijke informatie.

description:
Marie-H├йl├иne Audoye, jeune et jolie azur├йene de 22 ans, disparait lors de sa tourn├йe des pharmacies ├а Monaco le 21 mai 1991. 
Entre enqu├кte rallong├йe, fausse piste, faux t├йmoignages et un suspect n┬░1 s├йrieux mais jamais ├йcrou├й ou mis en examen, ce cold case fran├зais vieux de 31 ans reste un myst├иre et un cauchemar pour la famille de Marie-H├йl├иne, et surtout sa m├иre qui se bat pour obtenir des r├йponses et pour que la disparition de sa fille ne tombe pas dans l'oubli. 
Un espoir renait  en ce mois de mai 2022, lorsqu'on apprend que le dossier va ├кtre repris par la cellule cold case mise en place en mars 2022 ├а Nanterre.

title: Laken Riley Kidnapped, Murdered While on Morning Jog - What We Know
description:
If youтАЩre ever injured in an accident, you can check out Morgan & Morgan. You can start your claim in just a click without having to leave your couch. To start your claim visit  https://ForThePeople.com/CrimeFix

Laken Riley, a 22-year-old woman, went out for a run last month but did not return home as expected. Concerned about her whereabouts, one of Riley's friends contacted the University of Georgia Police. Within 30 minutes of the report, officers located Riley in a wooded area off a trail, where she was found with visible injuries. The following day, UGA police announced that Jose Antonio Ibarra had been charged in connection with Riley's murder and kidnapping.

Subscribe for more Law&Crime: https://bit.ly/LawAndCrimeNetwork

In this episode of Crime Fix, a daily show that explores notable crime stories, Law&Crime's Angenette Levy discusses the available details of the case with retired NYPD cold case sergeant Joe Giacalone. They examine the timeline of events surrounding Laken Riley's disappearance, the police response, and the subsequent arrest of the suspect. Levy and Giacalone also provide insights into the investigative process and the potential next steps in the legal proceedings.

A crime that took more than three decades to solveтАж A teen, murdered in her own bed while her family slept downstairsтАж. The perpetrator only unmasked after thirty yearsтАжThe shocking truth finally comes to light.16-year-old Fawn Cox of Kansas City Missouri was murdered and then became a victim of necrophiliaтАж

Her family was oblivious to the ordeal taking place upstairs.  Initially, police found clues to a robbery gone wrongтАж but the brutality of the crime just didnтАЩt add up to a simple robbery. Did somebody have a personal vendetta against the popular teen? title: Agression du M23: le Chef dтАЩ├Йtat major g├йn├йral des FARDC ├аGoma pour remonter le moral des militaires
description:
Agression du M23 : le Chef dтАЩ├Йtat major g├йn├йral des FARDC ├а Goma pour remonter le moral des militaires

Ce 27 mai 2022- Le g├йn├йral dтАЩarm├йe C├йlestin Mbala Munsense, chef dтАЩ├Йtat major g├йn├йral des forces arm├йes congolaises (FARDC), est arriv├й ce vendredi 27 mai, ├а Goma, chef-lieu de la province du Nord-Kivu.
DтАЩapr├иs des sources, cette haute autorit├й militaire congolaise est arriv├й dans cette partie pour remonter le moral des troupes sur la ligne des fronts dans la vall├йe de Kibumba, contre le M23 et leurs alli├йs Rwandais.

Sur la ligne des fronts, apprend-t-on des sources locales, les ├йl├йments FARDC qui sont d├йtermin├йs ├а mettre fin ├а la r├йbellion du M23, qui s├йvit depuis quelques mois dans la province, ont ├йt├й assist├йs en vivre par des membres du gouvernement provincial et quelques bienfaiteurs.

La piste de lтАЩa├йroport de Bunia sera bient├┤t prolong├йe de 650m, annonce le gouverneurBient├┤t la piste de lтАЩa├йroport national de Murongo en ville de Bunia, chef-lieu de la province de lтАЩIturi, sera agrandie de longueur et de largeur par lтАЩentreprise Mo Gabaon appartenant ├а un op├йrateur ├йconomique iturien.

Cette annonce a ├йt├й faite ce vendredi 27 mai 2022 par le Gouverneur de lтАЩIturi, lieutenant g├йn├йral Luboya NтАЩkashama Johnny apr├иs avoir effectu├й une visite dтАЩinspection de la piste et de lтАЩusine de cette entreprise sens├йe ex├йcuter les travaux.├А en croire lтАЩautorit├й provinciale, une longueur de 650 m├иtres sera ajout├йe aux 1 850 m├иtres actuels pour que la ville de Bunia ait lтАЩa├йroport avec une piste capable de supporter lтАЩatterrissage des avions de gros tonnages.

title: CPD Cold Case: Elizabeth Dunlap
description:
Elizabeth Dunlap was found dead on December 31, 1976 in the South Austin neighborhood. Her two children were found alive next to her. We need your help to find the person responsible for Elizabeth's murder as we seek justice for her and her family.

We ask anyone with information about this case, or any open homicide investigation, to please call our anonymous tipline at (833) 408-0069 or send in a tip at CPDTip.com.

title: Cold Case at Carlton's Canyon - Rita Herron 1 (AudioBook)
description:
Two officers' badgesтАФand heartsтАФare on the line in Rita Herron's Cold Case at Carlton's Canyon

Sergeant Justin Thorpe has dedicated his life to justice and won't stop until he finds the vicious serial killer who has already claimed ten innocent lives. He works soloтАФuntil he joins forces with Sheriff Amanda Blair. The Texas Ranger can't let his desire for his coworker keep him from his mission, especially when Amanda's life is threatened.

Ten girls have vanishedтАФone for every year since Amanda graduated from Canyon High. And as she tries to fight her attraction to a man as independent as she is, a trap is being laid to make Amanda the final victim in a killer's terrifying endgameтАж.

title: Crime Patrol - рдХреНрд░рд╛рдЗрдо рдкреЗрдЯреНрд░реЛрд▓ рд╕рддрд░реНрдХ - Ep 829 - Murder At Midnight - 14th July, 2017
description:
Click here to Subscribe to SetIndia Channel : https://www.youtube.com/user/setindia?sub_confirmation=1
Click to watch all the episodes of Crime Patrol Dial 100 - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupzBi22rTZgQbnRMWVCrUEvP

Episode 829:
---------------------
Durga, a middle-aged woman, is stabbed to death at midnight. After committing the crime, the assailant disappears into the darkness. Her neighbours hear her cries and rush to her aid but it is too late as Durga bleeds to death. The police begin investigation into the murder and suspect that Satish is the murderer. However, the relationship between Durga and Satish was a complicated one as Durga treated Satish as her son. If so, why did Satish take such an extreme step and murder Durga? Watch this episode to find out. 

Crime Patrol:
---------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?'I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Arrest made in 1996 Bronx cold case
description:
Police have made an arrest in a cold case murder dating back more than 25 years.

The NYPD arrested 66-year-old Gregory Fleetwood in connection with the 1996 murder of Jasmine Porter in the Bronx.

Porter, who was 36, was found dead inside her home on Davidson Avenue.

Police said she had bruises on her neck.

title: рд╕рдордЭреМрддрд╛ | Crime Patrol | Viewer's Choice
description:

https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupzmzTUmYFZJe4UhLkm23APh

Relive the best episodes of your favorite crime-thriller show, Crime Patrol.  

About the show:
--------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

About Crime Patrol :
-----------------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: City Crime | Crime Patrol | Aim-Part 2 | Jodhpur | Full Episode
description:
Click here to Subscribe to SET India Channel: https://www.youtube.com/user/setindia?sub_confirmation=1

Watch special episodes of Crime Patrol handpicked from different corners of India

About the show Crime Patrol:
------------------------------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Sikhs, Spies and Murder: Investigating IndiaтАЩs alleged hit on foreign soil | Foreign Correspondent
description:
When Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau stood up and accused India of being behind the killing of a Sikh activist on Canadian soil last year the world took notice. To have a head of state call out another country for effectively a state sponsored assassination was eye popping. Then, months later, US authorities said an Indian agent was involved in a murder attempt on an American Sikh in New York. Now Foreign Correspondent can reveal Australian authorities are also speaking to the Sikh community here.  

This week South Asia Correspondent Avani Dias travels to Punjab where tensions are high and the authorities are watching. This is the Sikh homeland where a banned separatist movement is fighting to create its own independent nation of Khalistan. Avani visits the family home of the man murdered in Canada Hardeep Singh Nijjar. and learns of unusual activity in the lead up to his killing. She also gains rare access to the movement's leaders, viewed as extremists by Indian officials, who are in no doubt the Modi government is targeting Sikh separatists around the world including Australia.

title: Oldest Cold Case FINALLY Solved In 2023 Mary Agnes Moroney
description:
After almost a century, the oldest cold case on record has finally been solved with the help of forensic science and extensive investigations. Mary Agnes Moroney, a victim of a heinous crime, can now rest in peace, as her case is closed and justice is served. This historical crime investigation utilized criminal profiling, homicide detectives, and DNA evidence to bring closure to the case. The breakthrough in the cold case, through forensic evidence analysis, is a significant achievement in the criminal justice system and has solved one of the greatest unsolved mysteries in true crime history. The work of the cold case unit and the reopening of the case is a testament to the importance of crime solving and case closure.

title: Crime Patrol - рдХреНрд░рд╛рдЗрдо рдкреЗрдЯреНрд░реЛрд▓ рд╕рддрд░реНрдХ - Case 7 / 2017 - Episode 760 - 21st January, 2017
description:
Subscribe to setindia channel for daily entertainment dose
https://www.youtube.com/user/setindia?sub_confirmation=1
Click to watch all the episodes of Crime Patrol Satark  -  https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupza0aEZ_FKj0mBguCdtwU_c
In today's episode of Crime Patrol, watch the investigation of a multiple murder case. Sangita is a widow who stays along with her daughter Aarti. Sangita's niece Vaishali and nephew Rohit often stay in her house during nights. Once, on a winter morning, the police find Sangita, Aarti, Vaishali and Rohit's dead bodies in the house. While investigating, the police find out that Sangita had an affair with an anonymous person. Want to know more? Then stay tuned in and find out here.
Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, тАЬIt should not have happenedтАЭ.Would knowing the тАЬWhyтАЭ behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he looks at meтАЭ, тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he/she is behavingтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she is out of his/her mindтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she has gone crazyтАЭ. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

Show Name: Crime Patrol
Host: Divyanka Tripathi Dahiya
Producers: Prem Krishen Malhotra, Sunil Mehta, Vipul D. Shah, Anirban Bhattacharyya

About Crime Patrol :
-----------------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Consentement et agression sexuelle
description:
ЁЯШН ABONNEZ-VOUS POUR RECEVOIR NOS PROCHAINES VID├ЙOS EN EXCLUSIVIT├Й ЁЯСНЁЯП╜

Pour plus d'information, rendez-vous sur https://violences-sexuelles.info/
Une initiative du CRIAVS ├Оle-de-France (https://criavs.fr) / H├┤pitaux de Saint-Maurice, en partenariat avec l'Association Une Vie (https://1vie.org)

+++
Facebook : https://www.facebook.com/infoviolencesex/
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/violences_sexuelles/
Twitter : https://twitter.com/violences_sex
+++

On a tous connu ce moment o├╣ on se demande si on a vraiment envie de faire l'amour...
Et l'autre, est-ce qu'il se pose la question ? Et est-ce qu'il en a vraiment envie ?
Et qu'est-ce que c'est dire oui ? ├А quoi est-ce que je dis oui, d'ailleurs ? Et comment dire non ? Et comment dire stop ?
Et si j'ai pas dit non, est-ce que c'est un viol ?

Le consentement ├а une relation sexuelle, ├зa pose un tas de questions. Et autant vous pr├йvenir tout de suite, les r├йponses sont pas si claires que ├зa. Mais avec ce site, on va essayer d'y r├йpondre, de vous donner des outils, et de vous aider ├а y voir plus clair.

Cette histoire de consentement ├а une relation sexuelle, elle date pas d'aujourd'hui. Seulement, avant, on se posait moins de questions. Ben oui, le p├иre de famille d├йcidait pour tout le monde : sa femme et ses enfants, personne n'avait son mot ├а dire.
Et dans beaucoup de soci├йt├йs aujourd'hui encore, c'est le cas : beaucoup de jeunes filles et de femmes doivent encore se plier au bon vouloir des hommes. Mais ├зa ├йvolue dans le bon sens !

Dans notre soci├йt├й, beaucoup de filles et de gar├зons ont connu ces lendemains de soir├йes o├╣ on se r├йveille ├а c├┤t├й de quelqu'un et on se dit "oups, j'aurais peut-├кtre pas d├╗"... Pour autant, entre regretter et ├кtre victime de viol, il y a un foss├й, parfois difficile ├а d├йlimiter. Alors, comment savoir ?

Et puis d'abord, qu'est-ce que c'est un viol ?

Pour la loi fran├зaise, c'est tout acte de p├йn├йtration sexuelle, de quelque nature qu'il soit, commis sur la personne d'autrui par violence, contrainte, menace ou surprise. Donc un viol, c'est pas forc├йment commis par un homme, et la victime c'est pas forc├йment une femme. Quant ├а la p├йn├йtration, elle peut avoir lieu dans la bouche ou dans l'anus, pas forc├йment dans le vagin. Et c'est pas forc├йment un sexe d'homme qui p├йn├иtre, ├зa peut ├кtre un doigt ou un objet...
Maintenant, pour les circonstances :
La violence, on sait ce que c'est : les coups et les cris, c'est ce qu'on voit le plus souvent dans les films.
La contrainte, c'est plus compliqu├й. C'est pas forc├йment quelqu'un qui va vous tenir avec ses mains. On peut tenir quelqu'un avec des mots, avec des id├йes. Si on est trop jeune, par exemple, on va ├кtre plus facilement impressionnable.
La menace, on a un peu du mal ├а la distinguer de la contrainte. ├Зa peut ├кtre un chantage ou une intimidation. Mais ├зa peut aussi ├кtre un cadeau, c'est pas forc├йment agressif.
Et la surprise, c'est simplement quand on ne s'y attend pas.

La punition pour un viol, elle est tr├иs lourde, en France. ├Зa peut aller jusqu'├а 15 ans de prison, et m├кme 20 ans ou 30 dans certains cas. C'est donc pas une mince affaire.

Maintenant, on sait ce que c'est que le viol. Mais on sait toujours pas ce que c'est que le consentement. D'ailleurs, le terme consentement n'apparait pas dans la loi quand on parle de sexualit├й.

Quand est-ce qu'on est d'accord ? ├А quoi est-ce qu'on est d'accord ?

D'abord, il faut ├кtre assez grand pour pouvoir consentir, on a une vid├йo l├а-dessus, que je vous invite ├а regarder apr├иs. Et il faut aussi ├кtre capable de consentir. Si je suis compl├иtement bourr├й, je vais pas ├кtre capable de discernement, c'est-├а-dire que je vais pas pouvoir clairement ├кtre d'accord. Si je dors, je suis pas non plus capable d'├кtre d'accord.

Si dans mon sommeil, quelqu'un vient me tripoter ou si je d├йcide d'aller tripoter quelqu'un qui dort, c'est pas un viol, il y a pas eu consentement, mais c'est quand m├кme interdit. ├Зa s'appelle une agression sexuelle. Et si je me mets ├а poil devant quelqu'un qui l'a pas demand├й, ├зa s'appelle aussi une agression sexuelle, et ├зa aussi c'est ill├йgal.

En gros, pour que ce soit l├йgal, il faut que l'autre soit clairement d'accord. Et ├зa, c'est pas toujours facile de le savoir...

title: 3 Major Developments in Execution-Style Murder of Pregnant Teen Hours From Delivery
description:
Savanah Soto was hours away from being induced to give birth to her first child when she and her boyfriend, Matthew Guerra, were shot to death last December. Christopher Preciado, 19, is charged with their murders and his parents are charged with helping move the bodies of Soto and Guerra. This week, Preciado's parents asked that their bail be reduced. Law&Crime's Angenette Levy talks with former prosecutor Josh Ritter about three developments in the case in this episode of Crime Fix тАФ a daily show that delves into the biggest stories in crime.

title: Cold Case Cast Then And Now 2021
description:
Cold Case is an American police procedural crime drama television series which ran on CBS from September 28, 2003 to May 2, 2010. The series revolved around a fictionalized Philadelphia Police Department division that specializes in investigating cold cases.The show is set in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, and follows Detective Lilly Rush (Kathryn Morris), a homicide detective with the Philadelphia Police Department, who specializes in "cold cases", or investigations which are no longer being actively pursued by the department. Rush was initially partnered with Detective Chris Lassing (Justin Chambers) in the first five episodes and then with Detective Scotty Valens (Danny Pino) for the remainder of the series. They work under Lieutenant John Stillman (John Finn) and are assisted by other detectives from their squadтАФNick Vera (Jeremy Ratchford), Will Jeffries (Thom Barry), and beginning in season three, Kat Miller (Tracie Thoms).
Usually, each episode would focus on a single investigation. All cases involved murders committed in Philadelphia, although investigations occasionally required travel outside the city. Cases were also spread out over much of the previous century, with some as recent as a year or two old and others dating back to the 1910s. Generally, an investigation would begin when the police received a new lead, or "new direction", on a case.

title: Crime Patrol - рдХреНрд░рд╛рдЗрдо рдкреЗрдЯреНрд░реЛрд▓ рд╕рддрд░реНрдХ - Ep 779 - Case 19/2017(Part 1)  - 18th Mar, 2017
description:
Click here to Subscribe to SET Channel : https://www.youtube.com/user/setindia?sub_confirmation=1
Click to watch all the episodes of Crime Patrol - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupza0aEZ_FKj0mBguCdtwU_c
In today's episode of Crime Patrol, watch the investigation of a murder case from Mumbai. The police find a dead body of a woman in a housing society. Within a week, the police find another dead body in different location. While investigating, the police find out that the bodies belong to Payal and Swati. The police learn that Payal used to work in a massage centre. Will the police be able to find the murderer? Stay tuned in to find the answer.
Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?'I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

CPD Cold Case: Veronica Williams and Brenda Graham
description:
Veronica Williams was found dead in March of 2007 in the 10100 block of South Wentworth. As detectives investigated her murder, they discovered DNA linked to the murder of Brenda Graham, who was killed in October of 1999. Both cases remain unsolved, but we have not forgotten.

We ask anyone with information about these cases, or any open homicide investigation, to please call our anonymous tipline at (833) 408-0069 or send in a tip at CPDTip.com.

title: Vous allez ├кtre choqu├йsтАж                    #histoirevrai #histoirefolle #horreur #agression
Crimewatch UK - 1990 Rape Cold Case Finally Solved in 2022!
description:
Paul Shakespeare was finally caught for the rape of an 18 year old in bushes along a public footpath in Cheltenham on April 29th 1990. This crimewatch episode aired in January 2008, but despite many leads and DNA taken from the scene, the rapist evaded capture for a further 13 years. 

It wasn't until 2021 that they finally caught their man due to a completely unrelated crime, the possession of an "offensive weapon". Were it not for this crime, the perpetrator would likely never have been caught. 

The victim, now 50, is still suffered psychologically from the event. The rape obviously petrified her at the time, with the mental horror causing her to nearly commit suicide. She still has not told her family due to the sheer violation and embarassment she feels from the rape.

Gary Shakespeare was finally sentenced in January 2022 to 9 years in prison, to the relief of the victim. Let me know what you think in the comments!

The news article can be found here: https://news.sky.com/story/paul-shakespeare-man-jailed-for-1990-rape-of-teenager-who-was-walking-her-dog-12518586

About The CID :
The first thrilling investigative series on Indian Television is today one of the most popular shows.  Dramatic and absolutely unpredictable, C.I.D. has captivated viewers over the last eleven years and continues to keep audiences glued to their television sets with its thrilling plots and excitement. Also interwoven in its fast-paced plots are the personal challenges that the C.I.D. team faces with non-stop adventure, tremendous pressure, and risk, all in the name of duty. The series consists of hard-core police procedural stories dealing with investigation, detection, and suspense. The protagonists of the serial are an elite group of police officers belonging to the Crime Investigation Department of the police force, led by ACP Pradyuman, played by the dynamic Shivaji Satam along with Daya and Abhijit. While the stories are plausible, there is an emphasis on dramatic plotting and technical complexities faced by the police. At every stage, the plot throws up intriguing twists and turns to keep the officers on the move as they track criminals, led by the smallest of clues.

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

description:
Shanda Vanderark questioned by her attorney on the witness stand. See parts before this and the parts I'll post after this for more context, they are posted in chronological order. I'll post the remaining parts of her full testimony in the next days. I'll also post the complete testimony of her son Paul Ferguson on the witness stand after that. He was found guilty as well.

If you liked this video, please leave a like, subscribe, comment, share & set the notification bell to ALL so you won't miss any new videos & premieres! You can now become a member of the channel too and give Super Thanks if you liked a video! This wil help me to continue making videos.

Please let me know what you think about her testimony in the comments below.

Heartbreaking.. Michigan woman Shanda Vander Ark was found guilty of murder and child abuse in the starvation┬аdeath of her disabled 15-year-old son┬аwho weighed just 69 pounds. 

The Muskegon County Circuit Court jury deliberated just over an hour before convicting┬аShanda Vander Ark, 44, of Norton Shores in the July 6, 2022, death of Timothy Ferguson. 

An autopsy determined the teenager died from malnourishment and hypothermia. The medical examiner ruled his death a homicide. 

Shanda's son Paul Ferguson was also convicted and has been sentenced to 30-100 years in prison. Paul Ferguson received the sentence after pleading guilty in December to one count of first-degree child abuse in the death of his 15-year-old brother Timothy Ferguson. Paul faced a potential sentence of up to life in prison, but the sentencing guidelines call for a term of 9-15 years. However, the judge's discretion was that this case was so serious that it called for him to be sentenced to 30-100 years. 

As part of a plea deal with the Muskegon County Prosecutor's Office, Paul testified against his mother, Shanda Vander Ark, at her trial in December. 

Vander Ark was convicted of neglecting Timothy so severely that he died in the basement of their home. Timothy was described by his mother as having high-functioning autism, ADHD, bipolar disorder, and several other mental ailments. 

According to Chief Trial Attorney for Muskegon County Matt Roberts, their office also agreed not to bring further charges against Paul, such as murder, in exchange for his guilty plea.

title: Doctor Accused of Poisoning Wife Identified as 'Widower' Before Murder: Police
description:
Former Mayo Clinic pharmacist Dr. Connor Bowman is charged with murdering his wife, Betty Bowman, last August. Police say Bowman poisoned Betty with medicine he ordered online and then tried to cover his tracks. Detectives now say Bowman was calling himself a widower before Betty died. Law&CrimeтАЩs Angenette Levy looks at the newly revealed evidence with forensic death investigator Joseph Scott Morgan in this episode of Crime Fix тАФ a daily show covering the biggest stories in crime.

description:

https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupzmzTUmYFZJe4UhLkm23APh

Relive the best episodes of your favorite crime-thriller show, Crime Patrol.  

About the show:
--------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

description:
Click here to Subscribe to SET Channel : https://www.youtube.com/user/setindia?sub_confirmation=1
Click to watch all the episodes of Crime Patrol Satark - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupza0aEZ_FKj0mBguCdtwU_c
Today's episode continues with the search of ShikhaтАЩs murderer. While investigating the case, the police find out that ShikhaтАЩs family had prohibited her from going to her college in the past. Sumit clears it to the police that he has not killed Shikha. Will the police be able to find the murderer? Stay tuned in to find the answer.
Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?'I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Fourteen Trump Officials Are Currently Accused Of Criminal Conduct
description:
According to the latest count, fourteen different Trump cabinet members and White House officials are either under investigation for violations of federal law, or they have been accused of breaking federal laws. The laws that these officials broke are all the same: The Hatch Act. And while it may seem small, it just goes to show that this administration has no regard for the rule of law. Ring of Fire's Farron Cousins discusses this.

title: Trump attorneys descend into disaster at criminal trial
description:
Former President Donald TrumpтАЩs lawyer may be losing what many attorneys would consider one of the most important things to have: credibility. ItтАЩs no secret that the former president might not be the easiest client to represent but TrumpтАЩs attorney, Todd Blanche, might be risking his reputation to do so. Judge Juan Merchan seemed frustrated with Blanche during a hearing this week to determine whether or not Trump violated a gag order in his first criminal trial. In response to BlancheтАЩs claim that Trump was attempting to comply with the judgeтАЩs orders, Judge Merchan told the attorney that heтАЩs losing credibility with the court. MSNBC's Brian Tyler Cohen takes a closer look at what went down and what this could mean for TrumpтАЩs lawyers and their reputations. title: Criminals Who Are STILL On the Run in 2024...
description:
On February 21st, Australian police finally caught the convicted murderer, Graham Potter, who had been on the run for 12 years. A convicted killer, he had been evading conspiracy to murder charges since 2010. Investigators later found that he had attempted to change his appearance and demeanour to avoid detection - but was eventually found in a dilapidated house in Ravenshoe, in the far north of Queensland. Potter, however, is one of many criminals who go on the run and manage to avoid capture for years, and sometimes even decades. In todayтАЩs video, weтАЩll be exploring two terrifying cases of criminals still on the run.

title: A Killer From A Cold Case Uncovered By A Psychic? | Psychic Investigators | Full Episode
description:
A detective asks a psychic to help him with a case that he has been unable to solve. The psychic offers her help with an older case of his instead, provides some new details, and possibly uncovers the murderer.

Do you believe in psychics and their contribution to the investigation?

Psychic Investigators - From Season 1 Episode 3 "Margie Calciano": Detective Robert Wanner consults psychic Lauren Thibodeau to help with a case that has left him stumped.  Surprisingly she instead offers clues on a cold case thatтАЩs been worrying Wanner for years.  ThibodeauтАЩs visions offer obscure clues: she sees a map with a bead of light traveling along a highway from New York to Chicago, a truck driver and the Brooklyn bridge.  Using old-fashioned police work, Wanner deciphers the clues one by one which lead him to a killer several states away.

Real-life detective thrillers take on a supernatural turn in Psychic Investigators, a documentary series about actual dramatic crimes that are solved through the unlikely combination of hi-tech detective work and the paranormal powers of a psychic.

In each episode, one amazing story is told from two very different points of view тАУ the detective and the psychic. Featuring crimes committed in the USA and the United Kingdom, Psychic Investigators juxtaposes the psychicтАЩs story - coloured with emotion, empathy and mystery, with the copтАЩs tale тАУ dominated by logic, evidence and reason. 

These spellbinding stories, interwoven with suspense, intrigue, and twists and turns, feature stylized dramatic reconstructions, unique archive and compelling interviews with key characters. Playing like supernatural thrillers, these shows make the hairs on the back of your neck stand on end.

title: Ventura PD solves 33-year-old cold case homicide
description:
After over three decades, the Ventura Police Department (VPD) has made a significant breakthrough in the 1991 murder case of Danielle Clause. Using advanced forensic genetic genealogy techniques, law enforcement has identified Larry Devon Welch as the perpetrator, which is a pivotal moment in resolving this long-standing mystery.

тАЬThrough extensive collaboration with local and national law enforcement agencies and nonprofits, itтАЩs with great pride that I share this success story,тАЭ said Ventura Police Chief Darin Schindler. тАЬFrom the initial investigation in 1991 to recent advancements in forensic techniques, IтАЩm honored to highlight the perseverance of detectives as they continued to seek justice for the victim and her family.тАЭ

On July 16, 1991, the body of 42-year-old Clause was found on the hillside located at the top of Tioga Drive near downtown Ventura. The autopsy showed that she had been sexually assaulted and had died due to multiple blunt-force injuries to her head. Once investigators at the time explored every avenue, the case was suspended and considered cold.

In 2021, Ventura Police detectives and forensic specialists retested crime scene evidence for DNA. Forensic genetic genealogy was pursued, and a family tree was developed. Phenotyping was used to verify distinct characteristics of the suspect, and after collecting family DNA samples, Larry Welch was positively identified. 

Welch passed away in 1999. There was no known connection between Welch and Clause at the time of her murder.

тАЬMy sister was so much more than a victim of a brutal murder. She was artist, a daughter, a sister, a mother, and a wife. She was a good person with a mighty soul, and she was taken way too young,тАЭ shared Marcie Forte, DanielleтАЩs sister. тАЬI didnтАЩt really believe that the police were going to solve this, because there are other crimes being committed all the time. I was proven wrong because the Ventura Police and everyone associated with this cold case did a phenomenal job and I am so grateful. IтАЩm so grateful that I lived to see at least a meter of justice and that they found out who did this.тАЭ

The Ventura Police DepartmentтАЩs unwavering commitment to securing justice for victims and their families endures, regardless of the elapsed time. Presently, VPD has over 25 cold cases, spanning homicides, missing persons, and unidentified deceased individuals.

For more information about each case, visit CityofVentura.ca.gov/ColdCases. If you have any new information, please email coldcase@venturapd.org.

title: Agression du 22 novembre 1970 : ┬л elle a eu lieu avec lтАЩaval de S├йkou Tour├й ┬╗, dit Aliou Barry
description:
La Guin├йe comm├йmore ce lundi, 22 novembre 2021, le 51├иme anniversaire de lтАЩagression portugaise du 22 novembre 1970 sur son territoire. A cette journ├йe de souvenirs douloureux et dтАЩ├йmotion qui font remonter les tristes souvenirs de cette tentative de d├йstabilisation du r├йgime S├йkou Tour├й ourdi par une puissance colonel (le Portugal), mais aussi la vague de r├йpressions orchestr├йe en Guin├йe par le r├йgime en place contre ┬л les complices ┬╗ de cette agression, Guineematin.com est ├а la rencontre de Aliou Barry, chercheur et directeur du CAES (centre dтАЩappui et dтАЩ├йtudes strat├йgiques). Notre interlocuteur assure que lтАЩattaque portugaise contre la Guin├йe a bel et bien eu lieu. Mais, il est aussi formel sur le fait que le chef de lтАЩEtat guin├йen de lтАЩ├йpoque, S├йkou Tour├й, ├йtait inform├й de ladite attaque. Et, il a voulu faire de cette agression un atout pour ├йliminer des adversaires politiques.

┬л Le 22 novembre est une date qui a permis ├а S├йkou Tour├й dтАЩop├йrer une large purge au sein de lтАЩ├йlite guin├йenne, quтАЩelle soit ├а la fois militaire ou politique. AujourdтАЩhui, toute la documentation existe pour dire que la nuit du dimanche 21 au 22 novembre, il y a 6 navires portugais qui ont accost├й aux larges de Conakry. Mais, avant lтАЩagression du 22 novembre, les Guin├йens de lтАЩext├йrieur s'├йtaient regroup├йs au sein du Front de lib├йration nationale de la Guin├йe qui ├йtait bas├й ├а Dakar et qui ├йtait dirig├й par monsieur David Soumah. CтАЩest lui et dтАЩautres Guin├йens qui ├йtaient contre le r├йgime en place qui ont cherch├й ├а renverser S├йkou Tour├й. Il sтАЩav├иre quтАЩ├а lтАЩ├йpoque, en Guin├йe, le PAIGC (Parti Africain de lтАЩInd├йpendance de la Guin├йe et du Cap-Vert) avait une base arri├иre en Guin├йe et ├йtait soutenu par S├йkou Tour├й dans la perspective de la lib├йration de la Guin├йe Bissau et des ├Оles du Cap-Vert. Et cтАЩest Amical Cabral qui dirigeait ce mouvement bas├й ├а Conakry. Il se trouvait aussi que pendant ces actions de lib├йration, le PAIGC a fait prisonnier quelques portugais notamment le maire de Lisbonne. Donc, le gouvernement portugais de lтАЩ├йpoque sтАЩest rapproch├й de lтАЩopposition guin├йenne (le Front de lib├йration de la Guin├йe) et ils ont envisag├й une action ├а la fois de lib├йration de leurs d├йtenus et aider la diaspora guin├йenne ├а renverser S├йkou Tour├й. CтАЩest ainsi que pendant des mois, il y a eu des r├йunions ├а Lisbonne, ├а Dakar et ├а Abidjan et pr├иs de 250 Guin├йens ont ├йt├й mobilis├йs. On les a envoy├йs aux ├оles Soga au Cap-Vert o├╣ avec lтАЩaide du gouvernement portugais, il y a eu 6 navires qui ont accost├й ├а Conakry ├а 2 heures du matin, la nuit du 22 novembre ┬╗, explique Aliou Barry.

┬л Selon la documentation quтАЩon a trouv├й, il y a eu m├йsentente. Le Portugal tenait ├а lib├йrer ses d├йtenus politiques et les Guin├йens voulaient profiter pour renverser S├йkou Tour├й. Mais, toute la documentation en notre possession prouve que S├йkou Tour├й a ├йt├й pr├йvenu par la CIA quтАЩil y aura une agression en Guin├йe. DтАЩailleurs, ├а 2 heures du matin, quand les gens ont d├йbarqu├й, curieusement, seule la pr├йsidence ├йtait ├йclair├йe. Le premier groupe qui est venu aux Cases Belle-vue nтАЩa pas trouv├й S├йkou Tour├й. Un autre groupe est parti lib├йrer les prisonniers politiques du Camp Bo├пro, le 3├иme groupe est parti au si├иge du PAIGC o├╣ un allemand a ├йt├й assassin├й. Le 4├иme est parti ├а lтАЩa├йroport de Conakry sans trouver ni Mig, ni avion. Il a d├йcid├й de ne rien faire. Il sтАЩest av├йr├й pendant ce temps que tous les moyens de communication ont une d├йfaillance. Ce qui est aussi curieux, c'est que ceux qui ont d├йbarqu├й ├а Conakry nтАЩont trouv├й aucune r├йsistance, parce quтАЩ├а lтАЩ├йpoque, m├кme ├а lтАЩinterne, le r├йgime de S├йkou Tour├й ├йtait d├йcri├й. LтАЩop├йration a foir├й et vers 8 heures du matin, les portugais ont d├йcid├й de se rembarquer avec les guin├йens qui ├йtaient disponibles dont le commandant Diallo Tierno qui dirigeait lтАЩop├йration et monsieur Siradio Diallo qui ├йtait pr├йsent. Malheureusement, nombreux sont ceux qui sont rest├йs ├а terre et ils ont ├йt├й arr├кt├йs par la milice populaire de S├йkou Tour├й qui en a fait toute une montagne ┬╗, a indiqu├й Aliou Barry.

┬л S├йkou Tour├й sтАЩest servi de cet ├йv├иnement pour d├йclarer quтАЩil y a eu une agression contre la Guin├йe. CтАЩest vrai que les portugais ont d├йbarqu├й ; mais, les Guin├йens aussi ont profit├й de lтАЩoccasion pour le renverser. Et, ├а partir de janvier 1971, S├йkou Tour├й a profit├й pour orchestrer une v├йritable purge au niveau de la classe politique. Dans toutes les villes de Guin├йe, il y a eu des pendaisons. A Conakry, au pont 8 novembre, il y a eu 4 hautes personnalit├йs qui ont ├йt├й pendues. CтАЩest vrai qu'il y a eu une agression ; mais, cтАЩest vrai aussi que S├йkou Tour├й ├йtait au courant de ce qui allait arriver. Cependant, il ne savait pas que les Guin├йens allaient en profiter pour le renverser. CтАЩest aussi une page de lтАЩhistoire guin├йenne qui est tr├иs sombre. Cela fait partie du devoir de m├йmoire et je crois que les historiens doivent rouvrir ce dossier en toute objectivit├й pour que les g├йn├йrations futures sachent ce qui sтАЩest pass├й le 22 novembre 1970 ┬╗

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Closing arguments in Trump criminal trial to begin
description:
Closing arguments are set to begin Tuesday in Donald Trump's New York criminal trial. CBS News investigative reporter Graham Kates has more.

bueno, solo un poquito.

.-┬┐Qu├й?

Me sent├н traicionada, as├н que no volv├н a verlo y trat├й de olvidarme de ├йl.

Los siguientes meses
