title: Affaire Bary: L'Heure du Crime
description:
26 mars 2004 il est 11h35, Laurent Bary, 35 ans, ├йleveur de poulets rentre chez lui ├а Lanneau pr├иs de Dijon. Alors qu┬┤il p├йn├иtre dans le salon il d├йcouvre une sc├иne d┬┤horreur, sa femme Val├йrie, 38ans, g├оt au sol, elle a le cr├вne fracass├й et a ├йt├й sauvagement poignard├йe de treize coups de couteau. Imm├йdiatement alert├йs les gendarmes trouvent pr├иs du corps de Val├йrie, l┬┤arme du crime, un couteau de boucher dont la lame mesure plus de vingt centim├иtres. Mais aucune empreinte, ni aucun ADN ne sera retrouv├й, comme si le meurtrier avait miraculeusement effac├й toute trace de son passage. Qui pouvait en vouloir ├а cette aide-soignante sans histoire ? Interrog├й Laurent Bary a un solide alibi, il a pass├й la matin├йe ├а livrer des poulets dans la r├йgion et l┬┤autopsie r├йv├иle que son ├йpouse a ├йt├й tu├йe une heure avant que l┬┤homme ne rentre au domicile conjugal. Tr├иs vite l┬┤enqu├кte s┬┤oriente sur l┬┤hypoth├иse d┬┤un cambriolage qui aurait mal tourn├й car plusieurs objets personnels de la victime ont disparu. 18 mois s┬┤├йcoulent, jusqu'├а ce que la montre de Val├йrie Bary soit retrouv├йe ├а quelques kilom├иtres seulement de la sc├иne du crime, au domicile d┬┤un proche du mari !

Meanwhile, a girl named Kajal is missing from her home and her parents has lodged the complaint of their missing child. Can Kajal be found? Who took her? To know all, watch the full episode.

Click to watch all the episodes of Crime Patrol - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupza0aEZ_FKj0mBguCdtwU_c

Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, тАЬIt should not have happenedтАЭ.Would knowing the тАЬWhyтАЭ behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he looks at meтАЭ, тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he/she is behavingтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she is out of his/her mindтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she has gone crazyтАЭ. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Crime Patrol - Discontented - Episode 412 - 5th September 2014
description:
Ep 412 - Crime Patrol Satark - In this UP special episode of Crime Patrol Satark, Host Anoop Soni explores the story of 2 Families who go through the same pain of losing one of their loved ones from their Family. Jagdish's Friend Lalit requests him to settle down as he lost his Wife Prerna and also talks about Sarita a divorcee who lost her Child. Jagdish's Father and Prerna get murdered. Who killed them? When this incident occurred in the house, nobody was there accept 2 labors, 2 people who came to meet Babuji and Sarita. Watch to find out. Watch all the latest videos of Crime Patrol Satark online on SonyLiv official website SonyLiv.com.

"Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, тАЬIt should not have happenedтАЭ.Would knowing the тАЬWhyтАЭ behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he looks at meтАЭ, тАЬI donтАЩt like the way he/she is behavingтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she is out of his/her mindтАЭ, тАЬI think he/she has gone crazyтАЭ. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

#gwilly #gwillyyt #purpysage #imtracyallen #DBHype #polyanime #finalform15


A powerful fox known as the Nine-Tails attacks Konoha, the hidden leaf village in the Land of Fire, one of the Five Great Shinobi Countries in the Ninja World. In response, the leader of Konoha and the Fourth Hokage, Minato Namikaze seals the fox inside the body of his newborn son, Naruto Uzumaki, making Naruto a host of the beast;[i] this costs Naruto's father his life, and the Third Hokage returns from retirement to become the leader of Konoha again. Naruto is often scorned by Konoha's villagers for being the host of the Nine-Tails. Due to a decree by the Third Hokage forbidding any mention of these events, Naruto learns nothing about the Nine-Tails until 12 years later, when Mizuki, a renegade ninja, reveals the truth to Naruto. Naruto then defeats Mizuki in combat, earning the respect of his teacher, Iruka Umino.[ii]

Shortly afterward, Naruto becomes a ninja and joins with Sasuke Uchiha, against whom he often competes, and Sakura Haruno, on whom he has a crush, to form Team 7, under an experienced sensei, the elite ninja Kakashi Hatake. Like all the ninja teams from every village, Team 7 completes missions requested by the villagers, ranging from doing chores and being bodyguards to performing assassinations.

After several missions, including a major one in the Land of Waves, Kakashi allows Team 7 to take a ninja exam, enabling them to advance to a higher rank and take on more difficult missions, known as Chunin Exams. During the exams, Orochimaru, a wanted criminal, invades Konoha and kills the Third Hokage for revenge. Jiraiya, one of the three legendary ninjas, declines the title of Fifth Hokage and searches with Naruto for Tsunade whom he chooses to become Fifth Hokage instead.

During the search, it is revealed that Orochimaru wishes to train Sasuke because of his powerful genetic heritage, the Sharingan. [iii] After Sasuke attempts and fails to kill his older brother Itachi,[iv] who had showed up in Konoha to kidnap Naruto, he joins Orochimaru, hoping to gain from him the strength needed to kill Itachi. The story takes a turn when Sasuke leaves the village: Tsunade sends a group of ninja, including Naruto, to retrieve Sasuke, but Naruto is unable to persuade or force him to come back. Naruto and Sakura do not give up on Sasuke; Naruto leaves Konoha to receive training from Jiraiya to prepare himself for the next time he encounters Sasuke, while Sakura becomes Tsunade's apprentice.

Part II
See also: List of Naruto chapters (Part II, volumes 28тАУ48) and List of Naruto chapters (Part II, 

#love 
Two and a half years later, Naruto returns from his training with Jiraiya. The Akatsuki starts kidnapping the hosts of the powerful Tailed Beasts. Team 7 and other Leaf ninja fight against them and search for their teammate Sasuke. The Akatsuki succeeds in capturing and extracting seven of the Tailed Beasts, killing all the hosts except Gaara, who is now the Kazekage. Meanwhile, Sasuke betrays Orochimaru and faces Itachi to take revenge. After Itachi dies in battle, Sasuke learns from the Akatsuki founder Tobi that Itachi had been ordered by Konoha's superiors to destroy his clan to prevent a coup; he accepted, on the condition that Sasuke would be spared. Devastated by this revelation, Sasuke joins the Akatsuki to destroy Konoha in revenge. As Konoha ninjas defeat several Akatsuki members, the Akatsuki figurehead leader, Nagato, kills Jiraiya and devastates Konoha, but Naruto defeats and redeems him, earning the village's respect and admiration.

With Nagato's death, Tobi, disguised as Madara Uchiha (one of Konoha's founding fathers), announces that he wants to capture all nine Tailed Beasts to cast an illusion powerful enough to control all humanity and achieve world peace. The leaders of the five ninja villages refuse to help him and instead join forces to confront his faction and allies. That decision results in a Fourth Shinobi World War between the combined armies of the Five Great Countries (known as the Allied Shinobi Forces) and Akatsuki's forces of zombie-like ninjas. The Five Kage try to keep Naruto, unaware of the war, in a secret island turtle near Kumogakure (Hidden Cloud Village), but Naruto finds out and escapes from the island with Killer Bee, the host of the Eight-Tails. At that time, NarutoтАФalong with the help of Killer BeeтАФgains control of his Tailed Beast and the two of them head for the battlefield.

title: Suspected serial killer pleads not guilty to 1998 cold case murder
description:
A suspected serial killer plead not guilty to a 1998 cold case murder in Broward.

Lucious Boyd is already on death row for the murder of another woman, and now Broward Sheriff's Office detectives connected Boyd to the murder of Eileen Truppner using DNA technology.

description:
Am 22.September 1981 kam Peter Perjesy aus Wattwil-Ulisbach nach einem abendlichen Tischtennis-Training im Schulhaus Risi nie zuhause an.
Die einzige Spur, die vom damals 14-J├дhrigen blieb, waren sein Velo sowie seine Jacke. Trotz umfangreicher Suche in der ganzen Gegend blieb er bis heute spurlos verschwunden. Die Ungewissheit ├╝ber das Schicksal einer verschwunden Person ist f├╝r die Angeh├╢rigen besonders qu├дlend. Es sei ein Wechselbad der Gef├╝hle, beschrieb es seine Mutter gegen├╝ber einer Reporterin.
Sie lebt heute im St. Galler Oberland. ┬лMit dem Tod kann man abschliessen, man kann an ein Grab gehen oder ein Ritual machen.┬╗ Aber wenn die Person nie gefunden werde, k├╢nne man nichts machen, um den Verlust zu bew├дltigen. Es bleibt ein Wechselbad von Hoffen, Resignieren und Trauern. Man komme dabei auf die wildesten Spekulationen, erz├дhlt eine andere Mutter eines Vermissten.
Hinweise sind an die Kantonspolizei Thurgau per Tel. 052 728 22 22 (Ausland 41 52 728 22 22), per Mail oder an jede Polizeidienststelle zu richten. SRF Beitrag 2013 - Hier hochgeladen gegen das Vergessen.

title: Murder Capital of the World | Living in San Pedro Sula, Honduras | Free Documentary
description:
Murder Capital of the World | Living in San Pedro Sula, Honduras | Free Documentary

World's Most Feared Gang in Guatemala - Meet the Maras: https://youtu.be/ymS1fMM9wB8

In the company of a pastor, an assassin, and a crime reporter, this film examines the fine line between good and evil in the world's most dangerous city.

Priest and furniture maker Daniel Pacheco works in one of the most dangerous cities in the world: San Pedro Sula, Honduras. He tries to save lives, but thatтАЩs no simple matter in a country with staggeringly high murder rates. The killings are countless, not just by the drug cartels but also by the police and the army. Pacheco lives in the midst of it, risking his own life.

Reporting murders is everyday business for TV journalist Orlin Castro. He seems comfortable with the nocturnal violence, but at the same time, he dreams of a different, quieter life. A hitman named Matathan talks openly about his profession. He says he has had enough and wants to start a new, pious existence. But Pacheco, who knows him well, doubts his sincerity.

Following these three men, Dutch-American filmmaker Loretta van der Horst, who was born in Honduras, gets frighteningly close to the horrific violence that no one seems able to end. If you donтАЩt value your own life, Pacheco explains, itтАЩs easier to kill others.

Also interwoven in its fast-paced plots are the personal challenges that the C.I.D. team faces with non-stop adventure, tremendous pressure, and risk, all in the name of duty. The series consists of hard-core police procedural stories dealing with investigation, detection, and suspense. The protagonists of the serial are an elite group of police officers belonging to the Crime Investigation Department of the police force, led by ACP Pradyuman, played by the dynamic Shivaji Satam along with Daya and Abhijit. While the stories are plausible, there is an emphasis on dramatic plotting and technical complexities faced by the police. At every stage, the plot throws up intriguing twists and turns to keep the officers on the move as they track criminals, led by the smallest of clues.

title: OKCPD Cold Case: Helen Gordon #shorts
description:
Raped. Beaten. Murdered. This was the tragic fate that ended 77 year-old Helen Gordon's life. Christmas Eve of 1975, Helen was with her family but never made it home. Her body was found two days later. The Oklahoma City Police Department has never given up on her case. OKCPD asks for your help. If you know anything, she and her family still deserve justice. 

Tips can be submitted to OKCPD anonymously through Crime Stoppers (405) 235-7300.

https://okccrimetips.com

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Ukraine : un tribunal international pour sanctionner le crime dтАЩagression ? тАв FORUM тАв TRAD FR
description:
LтАЩUkraine et ├а sa suite, la Commission europ├йenne militent pour la cr├йation dтАЩun Tribunal sp├йcial pour sanctionner le crime dтАЩagression contre lтАЩUkraine. Depuis les tribunaux de Nuremberg, lтАЩagression est consid├йr├й comme ┬л le crime des crimes ┬╗, mais il nтАЩa jamais ├йt├й poursuivi. La Cour p├йnale internationale qui enqu├кte sur les crimes de guerre en Ukraine nтАЩa pas de comp├йtence pour poursuivre le crime dтАЩagression. Les partisans dтАЩun tel tribunal sp├йcial consid├иrent que celui-ci pourrait cr├йer un important pr├йc├йdent pour sanctionner les guerres dтАЩagression. Les sceptiques mettent en garde sur le fait quтАЩun tel tribunal viendrait consacrer une justice internationale s├йlective qui ne sanctionnerait que les pariahs.

title: A 71-year-old suspect in a four-decades-old cold case has pleaded not-guilty to two counts of kidnap
description:
(25 Jan 2007) HEADLINE: 'Not guilty' plea for '64 race case suspect
---------------------------------------
CAPTION:  A reputed Ku Klux Klansman and former sheriff's deputy has plead not guilty to kidnapping charges in the 1964 deaths of two black hitchhikers in Mississippi. (Jan. 25)
----------------------------------------



[Notes:ANCHOR VOICE]
Moore//"This was bound to happen. The right people, at the right place, at the right time." 

IT MAY HAVE TAKEN FOUR DECADES, BUT THOMAS MOORE *FINALLY* GOT THE NEWS HE'D BEEN PRAYING FOR.

Gonzales or Official//We've handed-up an indictment. 

OFFICIALS SAY 71-YEAR-OLD JAMES FORD SEALE WAS INVOLVED IN A 19-64 DOUBLE MURDER IN THE DEEP SOUTH...A HORRIFIC CRIME THAT TOOK THE LIFE OF MOORE'S YOUNGER BROTHER, CHARLES.

Gonzales or Official//describes how they were killed.

BUT IT WAS AN INDICTMENT THAT ALMOST WASN'T.

THE CASE LAY DORMANT FOR 42-YEARS...UNTIL MOORE AND A DOCUMENTARY FILMMAKER STARTED INVESTIGATING.

Moore//"Truth and justice, that's what we wanted [cut to next bite] Each one of those trips brought us new hope. We kept digging."

THEY PORED OVER DOCUMENTS...INTERVIEWED WITNESSES...AND SEARCHED FOR SEALE...WHO, HAD...INCORRECTLY...BEEN REPORTED AS DEAD.

Mueller//They really figured it out.

A SECOND SUSPECT IN THE CASE....CHARLES MARCUS EDWARDS....WAS *NOT* CHARGED IN THE INDICTMENT.

Gonzales//I can't comment on that.

SOURCES CLOSE TO THE INVESTIGATION SAY EDWARDS IS REPORTEDLY COOPERATING WITH AUTHORITIES.

title: Pi├иge Mortel : Meurtre  au haras
description:
Fr├йjus, 30 septembre 2003. Il est 15h30 lorsque Rita Hug, une suisse-allemande de 51 ans, appelle la police compl├иtement affol├йe. Elle vient de d├йcouvrir son mari Martin Staub, un riche homme d┬┤affaires de 51 ans, gisant dans une mare de sang. L'homme a eu le cr├вne d├йfonc├й avant de mourir ├йtrangl├й. Sur place, les policiers ne trouvent aucun indice permettant d┬┤identifier le ou les agresseurs. Interrog├йe, la femme de la victime affirme avoir rendu visite ├а une amie dans l┬┤apr├иs-midi avant de rentrer chez elle et de d├йcouvrir la sc├иne de crime. Les policiers n┬┤ont aucune raison de douter de son t├йmoignage, d┬┤autant qu┬┤elle formait avec son mari un couple heureux, ├йpanoui, ├а la r├йputation irr├йprochable. Dans la maison les policiers ne trouvent aucune trace d┬┤effraction et aucun objet n┬┤a ├йt├й vol├й. L┬┤hypoth├иse du cambriolage est donc ├йcart├йe. Il semble que Martin Staub connaissait ses agresseurs et leur a ouvert la porte volontairement. Les policiers ne disposent d┬┤aucune piste s├йrieuse mais en interrogeant le personnel du couple, ils apprennent que Rita Hug, loin d┬┤├кtre une ├йpouse mod├иle, avait un amant. La piste du crime passionnel est envisag├йe. L┬┤amant est arr├кt├й mais l┬┤homme dispose d┬┤un solide alibi. L┬┤enqu├кte semble ├кtre dans une impasse quand l┬┤autopsie r├йv├иle que le crime a eu lieu vers midi. Une information capitale qui ne colle pas avec la version de Rita Hug sur cette journ├йe fatidique...
R├йalisateur : Delphine Welter

Watch special episodes of Crime Patrol handpicked from different corners of India

About the show Crime Patrol:
------------------------------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Miss Honduras murder: Maria Jose Alvarado and sister killed by jealous boyfriend
description:
Missing Honduran beauty queen Maria Jose Alvarado and her sister have been found dead, and were allegedly murdered by her sisterтАЩs boyfriend, Honduran police said on Wednesday.

Maria Jose Alvarado and her sister Sofia had been missing since they went to celebrate the birthday of SofiaтАЩs boyfriend, Plutarco Ruiz at a spa near Santa Barbara last Thursday, the Telegraph reported.

The two sisters were last seen leaving the party in a car without a licence plate, the BBC reported.

Ruiz was reportedly angered after watching his girlfriend dancing with another man at the party. The couple had a fight before Ruiz took out a pistol and shot dead Sofia. Maria tried to flee, but was shot twice in the back, the Telegraph reported.

The sisters were shot dead on the banks of the River Aguagua, El Pais reported. Their bodies were found on Wednesday.

Ruiz reportedly confessed to the murders of the two sisters and buried them with the help of Aris Valentin Maldonado. Both men have been arrested by Honduran police, the BBC reported.

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Agression du caporal Choolun: neuf suspects participent ├а lтАЩexercice de reconstitution des faits
description: Avisen Soobrayen, 20 ans, Yogesh Nathoo, 25 ans, Rehan Mooneea, 19 ans, et son fr├иre  Akilesh 18 ans,  Avishdave Mungur, 26 ans, Yeshay Toolsy, 19 ans, Farhaan Nabeebux 19 ans et Dovic St Mart, 18 ans et un mineur de 16 ans, sont retourn├йs au bypass de Goodlands pour un exercice de reconstitution des faits ce mardi 11 septembre. Ils ont avou├й avoir aid├й Cheetsing Gokhul, dit Adarsh, 23 ans, ├а agresser le policier qui les avaient interpell├й alors quтАЩils prenaient part ├а un rallye ill├йgal dimanche apr├иs-midi.  Adarsh Gokul avait crach├й au visage du caporal Choolun avant de lтАЩagresser.  Le principal suspect nтАЩ├йtait pas pr├йsent pour lтАЩexercice.  Il participera ├а la reconstitution lorsque son avocat sera disponible.

title: Team Justice Letter to State AGs Demanding Criminal Investigations of Trump & Co. for COVID Deaths
description:
Team Justice is a diverse group of individuals dedicated to equal justice for all and accountability for government officials who commit crimes or abuse their power or position of public trust. Team Justice was founded by Glenn Kirschner, a 30-year federal prosecutor who spent decades handling murder cases in the courts of the District of Columbia.

We've drafted a letter to all 50 state attorneys general and the AG for the District of Columbia demanding they open criminal investigations into Trump and members of his administrations for avoidable/preventable coronavirus deaths. 

We are asking all citizens to consider signing the letter if you believe state prosecutors should investigate Trump's gross mishandling of the coronavirus pandemic. The text of the letter is explained in this video and is listed below. To sign the letter, simple click on this link:

 https://forms.gle/Rktg7hqucgsgMABi6

Thank you, 

Team Justice

Dear Attorney General __________
We are writing to urge you to have your state law enforcement authorities open a criminal investigation into potential liability for avoidable/preventable coronavirus deaths in your state. Given the public reporting, we believe there is prima facie evidence that Donald Trump, Jared Kushner, Mike Pence and potentially other Trump administration officials are criminally liable
for, at a minimum, a low-level of homicide, such as negligent homicide/involuntary manslaughter. In our estimation, there certainly is adequate predication to open a criminal investigation into such matters.

Team Justice is a diverse group of people dedicated to honor, integrity and decency in public service, holding criminal government officials accountable for their crimes and, above all else, pursuing equal justice for all. There are signatories to this letter from each of the 50 states and the District of Columbia. Collectively, we seek accountability for any and all crimes of our
federal and state government officials, with the corresponding goal of restoring public trust, faith and confidence in government.

The founder of Team Justice, Glenn Kirschner, is a former career federal prosecutor who spent decades prosecuting murder cases as an Assistant United States Attorney for the District of Columbia. He also served as Chief of the Homicide Section of that office, supervising approximately 30 homicide prosecutors and overseeing all murder prosecutions in DC.

Without engaging in a full legal analysis (footnote), the publicly reported information about the grossly negligent mismanagement of the coronavirus pandemic by the Trump administration includes:
Donald TrumpтАЩs lies to the American people about the danger of the virus and its ease of transmission and corresponding ease of prevention (as revealed in the Bob Woodward audio recordings of conversations with Donald Trump); the decision by Mike Pence, then serving as head of the Coronavirus task force, to allow TrumpтАЩs dangerous lies to the American people to go uncorrected; the complicity of Jared Kushner who advocated letting the virus flourish because it was disproportionally affecting so-called тАЬblue statesтАЭ; etc. These are just some of the facts and
circumstances supporting opening a criminal investigation.
The families who lost loved ones to the coronavirus deserve and demand that the government officials responsible for allowing the pandemic to spread needlessly through our communities be held accountable. Accordingly, we respectfully implore you to open criminal investigations into
the conduct of government officials in an attempt to hold them accountable for any and all crimes supported by the evidence. Only a full, fair, ethical, aggressive, apolitical investigation can ensure accountability and help prevent future misconduct by government officials. Absent accountability for avoidable coronavirus deaths there can be no justice. Absent justice
there can be no healing for families who lost loved ones to the coronavirus.
We thank you for your time and attention to this most important matter and look forward to your reply.

Sincerely,

Team Justice
By: _____________________
Glenn Kirschner
Founder, Team Justice

(footnote) Although statutes vary from state to state, there are certain universal principles in assessing potential homicide
liability. On the lower end of the homicide-liability scale, there are offenses referred to alternatively as negligent
1. A negligent/grossly negligent/criminally reckless act OR a duty to act and a negligent/grossly negligent/reckless failure to act,
2. That act/failure to act is reasonably likely to result in death or serious bodily injury to another, which thereby,
3. Causes the death of another.
Importantly, the term тАЬcausationтАЭ is generally defined in the law as conduct that is a substantial factor in bringing
about the death.

Please consider becoming a #TeamJustice patron at:  https://www.patreon.com/glennkirschner

Subscribe to Swastik Productions India for more such videos - http://bit.ly/SubscribeSwastikProductions

Watch all episodes of Porus here - http://bit.ly/PorusAllEpisodes

Watch Purshottam, a.k.a Porus, portray his perpetual appetite for his motherland while taking on the fearsome legend of the West, Alexander The Great. The entire journey of Alexander carving his way to India, acquiring Indian allies, and then losing them while Porus prepares his country for a do-or-die battle is followed by the ruthless Battle of Hydaspes in a northwestern state of the Indian subcontinent.

This intriguing tale sets back to 350 BC and narrates the stark irony of how Porus and Alexander were born on the same day but were fostered with contrasting mindsets. Diverse characters from Greece and Indian history are brought to life and eventually the story fuses into a trembling climax leading to superbly depicting the courageousness of Indian emperors.

title: Patricia Kopta | FOUND ALIVE in Puerto Rico | Cold Case Solved | INTO THE MISSED
description:
Patricia Kopta was a street preacher known as тАЬThe SparrowтАЭ. Patricia went missing in 1992 in Ross Township, PA. She left her husband of 20 years, Bob Kopta with no answers at all. He reported her missing and even advertised about it in Puerto Rico, where she had frequently vacationed in the past. After 7 years, Bob had his wife legally declared dead. He never remarried. 

In 1999 Patricia was found in need wandering the streets of Puerto Rico and was taken into an adult care home. She refused to talk about her past or where she came from. But as the years passed and dementia set in, she began to leak details about her life. This lead to social workers contacting the Pennsylvania Police. After the DNA tests where done, they concluded that this was in fact Patricia Kopta. 

While Bob is happy to find out the truth and to know that she is being taken care of, he does not plan on going to visit her. He stated that he just wants to forget the past. 

PatriciaтАЩs sister Gloria has tried to speak with her on the phone, but Patricia is unable to hold a conversation given her dementia. Gloria plans to go visit her and give her a big hug and tell her that she loves her. 

What a relief for the family to find out that Patricia is still alive after all those years!!














Contact me:
Lynzie 
Intothemissed@gmail.com

I may have opinions on what happened to these people but in no way mean to cast blame upon anyone in the stories. All information stated is accurate to my knowledge but subject to change. Please show respect to all involved in these cases. Everyone is innocent until proven guilty.

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: A cold case detective searches for answers after womanтАЩs body found in yard waste bin in 2019
description:
Investigators in Pierce County are hopeful someone has details about a woman found dead in 2019 near Bonney Lake, as new tests on the person's remains are awaiting results.

On Aug. 28, 2019, on a then-vacant lot on 9th Street East just north of Lake Tapps, construction workers found body parts in a yard debris container that was sealed shut.

A forensic anthropologist determined the human remains belonged to a woman. As of Sept. 6, the department is waiting on results of genetic genealogy тАУ hoping her DNA will connect her to family members who submitted their own data to public database.

description:

title: Cold case surrounding 1971 fatal cabin fire solved by southern Indiana sheriff's office
description:
After more than 50 years, a mystery involving a fatal cabin fire has been answered thanks to a Southern Indiana sheriff's department.

The Jackson County Sheriff's Office worked to solve the cold case involving three teens on Dec. 18, 1971, who were staying in a cabin near the White River on the outskirts of Brownstown.

The cabin, built from railroad ties, was used as a hangout and for camping by local teenagers. Stanley Robison, 17, Jerry Autry, 19, and Mike Sewell, 16, were believed to be in the cabin when it caught fire 52 years ago.

Sewell's younger sister, Linda Pack, said her family has waited for answers.

title: Agression Rwandaise: Les FARDC/WAZALENDO neutralisent des terroristes M23RDF ├а MASISI ce 25/5/2024
description:
Agression Rwandaise: Les FARDC/WAZALENDO neutralisent des terroristes M23RDF ├а MASISI ce 25/5/2024

Les FARDC et les Jeunes r├йsistants wazalendo se sont affront├йs ├а l'arm├йe Rwandaise ce vendredi 24 mai dans le village de Bwanga , sur la colline de Lukala, en territoire de Masisi. Au cours des ces affrontements plusieurs ├йl├йments Rwandais ont ├йt├й neutralis├йs par les Fardc wazalendo. L'arm├йe loyalistes poursuivent toujours l'ennemi
Un calme pr├йcaire r├иgne ├а Kashuga, dans la localit├й de Mweso, territoire de Masisi, apr├иs des affrontements signal├йs dans cette r├йgion entre les ├йl├йments Wazalendo du mouvement NDC/R et les rebelles du M23.

Selon nos sources ├а Kashuga-Ibuga, les ├йchanges de tirs entre ces deux factions arm├йes ont provoqu├й une psychose au march├й central de Kashuga ce jeudi, jour de march├й, pendant plusieurs heures. Les habitants, pris de panique, ont d├йsert├й les lieux, craignant pour leur s├йcurit├й.

DтАЩautres sources indiquent quтАЩen dehors du centre de Kashuga, dтАЩautres collines surplombant Misinga sont sous le contr├┤le des ├йl├йments Wazalendo (VDP), qui se disent d├йtermin├йs ├а lib├йrer la r├йgion afin de permettre le retour des d├йplac├йs sur la route Mweso-Kalembe-Pinga.

Dans la chefferie des Bashali ├а Bweru, la pr├йsence des ├йl├йments Wazalendo a ├йt├й signal├йe apr├иs le retrait des rebelles du M23, qui occupaient pr├йc├йdemment cette r├йgion. Nos sources ├а Kivuye rapportent que les rebelles se sont retir├йs de cette zone pour se concentrer ├а Mpati et Kivuye centre.

Les m├кmes sources, contact├йes Estinfo.net, renseignent que ces retraits progressifs des rebelles du M23 dans plusieurs r├йgions de Masisi seraient le r├йsultat des offensives des militaires FARDC et des VDP depuis la semaine derni├иre dans plusieurs villages de Masisi. Certains rebelles se sont rendus avec leurs armes au g├йn├йral Jean-Marie, tandis que dтАЩautres ont commenc├й ├а ├┤ter leurs tenues militaires pour se d├йguiser en civils

title: Crimewatch Cronicles 22 Year cold case Murder Solved.
description:
Support the channel
https://www.patreon.com/truecrimereport

The discovery of Tracey WyldeтАЩs body at her flat in Barmulloch, north-east Glasgow, in November 1997 fuelled fears that a serial killer was targeting sex workers in the city.

Seven women were murdered in Glasgow between 1991 and 1998, all of whom were working in the sex industry at the time of their deaths. The killers of two of the women тАУ Margo Lafferty and Christine Dinnie тАУ were successfully prosecuted.

Zhi Min Chen had been due to stand trial at Glasgow high court but pleaded guilty on Wednesday to WyldeтАЩs murder.

Wylde, who had a young daughter, had gone into Glasgow city centre on 23 November 1997. The 21-year-old was last spotted on CCTV at about 3.20am the next morning in the cityтАЩs red-light area. Her body was discovered by friends at her flat the following day. There were marks and bruising around her neck, and the cause of death was found to be manual strangulation. The court did not learn how Wylde met her killer.

title: Unsolved: The Keddie Cabin Murders - Chilling Cold Case Mystery in Keddie
description:
The chilling tale of Unsolved: The Keddie Cabin Murders takes us back to a quiet town shattered by a heinous crime. In April 1981, the Sharp family's idyllic life in Keddie turned into a nightmare when a quadruple murder unfolded in Cabin 28 of the Keddie Resort. The haunting details of blood-soaked walls, bound victims, and a missing sibling paint a picture of darkness that still lingers.

The documentary delves into the lives lost - Glenna Sue Sharp, a brave mother, and her family members who sought refuge in Keddie. As the investigation unfolds, suspicions, rumors, and ties to criminal activities cloud the search for justice. Decades later, the quest for closure and resolution of this unsolved mystery continues, reminding us of the enduring impacts of unspeakable tragedy.

Join us as we unravel the heartbreaking tale of the Keddie Cabin Murders, a story of resilience, loss, and the unwavering pursuit of truth in the face of darkness.

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Tense moments in Ali Abulaban double murder trial
description:
There were tense moments inside the courtroom Thursday as testimony continued in the double murder trial involving former social media personality Ali Abulaban.  

Abulaban is charged with killing his wife Ana and her friend Ray Barron. Thursday was the third day in a row Abulaban has taken the stand.

For the majority of the day, the prosecution cross-examined him, during which time, there were a lot of tense interactions.

At one point, Abulaban got upset when the prosecution accused him of yelling the word тАШrespectтАЩ while he shot Ana and Barron, something he denies.

title: Brooklyn cold case killer gets 25 years to life in prison
description:
A 40-year-old man convicted in the 2004 murder of a Brooklyn teenager after a 2016 DNA analysis of the victim's fingernails linked him to the cold case was sentenced to the maximum of 25 years to life in prison Friday.

The naked body of 17-year-old Sharabia Thomas was discovered on the afternoon of February 11, 2004, inside two laundry bags on the side of an alleyway adjacent to 130 Palmetto Street in Bushwick.

The victim suffered blunt force trauma to her head, face and torso and had visible ligature marks on her wrists and ankles. The cause of death was determined to be asphyxia by neck compression. There was no evidence of a sexual assault.

Kwauhuru Govan, formerly of Gates Avenue in Bushwick, was convicted of second-degree murder. He learned his fate after the judge heard victim impact statements from Thomas' sisters.

title: Crime Patrol | Motive | Justice For Women | Full Episode
description:
Click here to Subscribe to SetIndia Channel: https://www.youtube.com/user/setindia?sub_confirmation=1

Click to watch all the special episodes of Crime Patrol:
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupyqFyV-YnilX3Qfa9tSEHad&disable_polymer=true

Watch special episodes of Crime Patrol handpicked from different corners of India.

About the show Crime Patrol:
------------------------------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like the way he looks at me', 'I donтАЩt like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: DNA Testing in West Memphis 3 Case #shorts
description:
In this episode of All Things Crime, Jared Bradley and George Jared delve deep into the unsettling case of the West Memphis Three. With meticulous detail, they recount the tragic murders of three young boys while visiting the site where the boys lived and where their bodies were found. They discuss the wrongful imprisonment of three teenagers and the subsequent legal battles that followed. From initial suspicions to recent developments in DNA testing, this discussion sheds light on the complexities and controversies surrounding this notorious case

https://www.m-vac.com/

All Things Crime is a new, comprehensive video series that will explore every aspect of crime and the ensuing investigation, one video interview at a time.  The host, Jared Bradley, is the President of M-Vac Systems, which is a wet-vacuum based forensic DNA collection system, and has experience traveling the world training all levels of law enforcement and crime lab DNA analysts in using the M-Vac to help solve crime.  Along the way he has met people from all walks of life and experience in investigating crimes, so is putting that knowledge to use in another way by sharing it in these videos.


If you are interested in more videos about the M-Vac, DNA and investigations, also check out the M-Vac's channel https://www.youtube.com/@MVacSystemsDNACollection

About The CID :
The first thrilling investigative series on Indian Television is today one of the most popular shows.  Dramatic and absolutely unpredictable, C.I.D. has captivated viewers over the last eleven years and continues to keep audiences glued to their television sets with its thrilling plots and excitement. Also interwoven in its fast-paced plots are the personal challenges that the C.I.D. team faces with non-stop adventure, tremendous pressure, and risk, all in the name of duty. The series consists of hard-core police procedural stories dealing with investigation, detection, and suspense. The protagonists of the serial are an elite group of police officers belonging to the Crime Investigation Department of the police force, led by ACP Pradyuman, played by the dynamic Shivaji Satam along with Daya and Abhijit. While the stories are plausible, there is an emphasis on dramatic plotting and technical complexities faced by the police. At every stage, the plot throws up intriguing twists and turns to keep the officers on the move as they track criminals, led by the smallest of clues.

title: Owaisi Dresses Down Amit Shah-introduced Criminal Bills In Lok Sabha; 'Threat To Indians...'
description:
AIMIM MP Asaduddin Owaisi lambasted the Modi government and slammed the three new criminal bills introduced by Union Home Minister Amit Shah in Lok Sabha. Owaisi termed the bills a threat to people of India and said that they represented sedition in a different Avatar. "The provisions of the bills are a threat to the civil liberty and rights,. Sweeping powers have been given to police to act as judge, jury and executor," he added. Watch highlights from his speech here.

title: Cold Case : verdwijning van Ringo Deman in Oostende
description:
De jonge man had een vaste job als buschauffeur bij тАЬDe LijnтАЭ  in Oostende. Na zijn werk is Ringo nog iets gaan drinken met vrienden. Omstreeks 17.00 uur kwam Ringo thuis in zijn appartement, dat hij deelde met een vriendin, op het Mac Leodplein in Oostende. Hij was moe en ging slapen. Een uur later stond zijn beste vriend Davy voor de deur. Volgens de verklaringen van de vriend Davy zijn ze met zijn wagen naar zijn appartement gegaan in de Roerdompstraat in Oostende om iets uit te praten. Volgens Davy zou Ringo hier te voet zijn weggegaan. Hij was boos en riep dat hij zelfmoord zou plegen. Dit is het laatste spoor van Ringo Deman.
De wagen en de fiets van Ringo blijven onaangeroerd, maar zijn gsm was het laatst actief op de mast van Loppem. Was Ringo daar zelf of enkel zijn gsm ?

In deze verdwijningszaak  werd aanvankelijk de piste van zelfmoord naar voor geschoven. Bijna 20 jaar later is er nog steeds geen lichaam gevonden en werd het dossier op vraag van het parket van West-Vlaanderen herlezen en geanalyseerd door de Cel vermiste personen.
Mensen uit het entourage van Ringo werden opnieuw verhoord . Hierbij kwam naar voor dat veel mensen twijfelen aan de piste van zelfmoord en dat de vermeende zelfmoordpogingen van toen enkel een roep om aandacht waren.  Ringo had ook geen familie meer waardoor er niemand voor hem opkwam.
Zijn vader was reeds overleden en zijn moeder was op dat ogenblik heel erg ziek en is kort na zijn verdwijning overleden. Hij had nochtans een hele goede band met zijn moeder.
Nu worden alle pistes open gehouden : zo kan Ringo een nieuw leven begonnen zijn,  zelfmoord hebben gepleegd of vermoord zijn.
De onderzoekers doen een oproep naar mensen die Ringo goed hebben gekend en die nog niet zijn gehoord door de politie.
Aan de mensen die iets weten maar tot nu toe nooit hebben durven of kunnen spreken, wordt gevraagd om zich te melden.

Ringo is 1m70 lang en struis gebouwd. Hij heeft donkerblond, kortgeknipt haar. De dag van zijn verdwijning droeg hij een bruine stoffen jas met een daim uitzicht, een donkere jeansbroek en wit/blauwe sportschoenen van het merk FILA .Hij droeg een ring aan ├й├йn van zijn pinken en heeft een tatoeage van een oranje gele zon, met diameter van 5 cm op de rechter schouder.

About the show Crime Patrol:
------------------------------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I donтАЩt like how he looks at me, 'I donтАЩt like how he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house, a husband and wife argue and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. FeelingsтАж expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Oliver Karafa, Lucy Li found guilty of 1st-degree murder, attempted murder
description:
Guilty on all charges. ThatтАЩs how a jury found married couple Lucy Li and Oliver Karafa.

Both were convicted of first-degree murder and attempted murder in the killing of 39-year-old Tyler Pratt and shooting of his pregnant girlfriend, Jordyn Romano.

First-degree murder carries an automatic life sentence in prison with 25 years before parole can be considered.

The jury deliberated for less than one day, returning to HamiltonтАЩs John Sopinka Courthouse Friday around 11 a.m. to deliver their verdict.

Romano, sitting in the courtroom with her supporters, cried out and hugged her mom. The family thanked each member of the jury as they left the courtroom.

Neither Li nor Karafa reacted to the juryтАЩs verdict.

title: NATO's Response to Russian Aggression in Ukraine
description: NATO is providing comprehensive support to Ukraine to help defend against Russia's invasion. This includes significant military assistance, humanitarian aid, and non-lethal support. NATO and its member states have delivered thousands of anti-tank weapons, air-defense missiles, small arms, and ammunition. Additionally, financial assistance and humanitarian aid, including medical supplies, have been sent to support Ukraine's defense efforts. NATO is also focused on long-term support, helping Ukraine transition from Soviet-era equipment to NATO standards, and enhancing the interoperability of Ukrainian forces with NATO allies. This robust support package underscores NATO's commitment to Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity in the face of ongoing aggression.

title: Mario Celaire - Cold Case Killers
description:
Mario Celaire, 31, killed Cassandra McDermott, 19, on October 25, 2001, in her motherтАЩs house in Granville Gardens, after an argument over her damaging a car he lent her.
He was found not guilty of her murder following a trial in 2002.
Yet after new evidence came to light he was reinvestigated by police, and pleaded guilty to the manslaughter of Cassandra at the Old Bailey on May 22, six years and six months later
